(271, 6, '2015-05-04 18:03:49', 'Takudzwa', 'Keith', 'Chaisewa', 286, '00263772669668', '00263772669668', '3135 of 158 Montgomery Drive\nProspect\nWaterfalls\nHarare\nZimbabwe', '', 'mobile_anytime', 'PKF Chartered Accountants (Zimbabwe)', 'Trainee Accountant', 'lt_6000', 'azn_31_35000', 'part_qualified_ACCA, Other', 'Part-qualified CTA', '/data/bakertilly/public_html/uploads/TKChaisewaCV.docx', '1991-07-23 00:00:00', 'male', 'Zimbabwean', 'Black_or_Black_British_-_African', 'No', 'yes', '2015-05-04 18:03:49', '0', 'I am a university graduate with over two years working experience in Audit and Tax Departments. I have worked on various audit clients, the likes of Lobels Bread Holdings, Supaswift t/a FedEx Zimbabwe, Thrive Micro-Finance, St Annes Hospital and Pulse Pharmaceuticals. Besides meeting the budget and submitting the agreed upon deliverables that is for example, the financial statements and reports to management, one of our core objectives of an audit was (is) to add value to clients. During the audit engagements, we would identify areas in which clients could improve for example their operational efficiency as well as identifying ways to minimize fruitless expenditure in addition to the identified weaknesses in the internal control environment.', 0, ''),
