(112, 'en', 1, 69, 1, NULL, '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', 1, '', 0, 0, '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', 'Corporate tax&nbsp;', '<p><font class=\"intro\" style=\"line-height: normal; \">You might represent a quoted international group or an owner managed business. Your corporate tax needs will range from routine annual compliance to specialist advice to plan and support your business strategies and transactions varying according to your particular sector and business circumstances.</font><span style=\"line-height: normal; \">&nbsp;</span><br style=\"line-height: normal; \"><span style=\"line-height: normal; \">&nbsp;</span><br style=\"line-height: normal; \"><span style=\"line-height: normal; \">There will be immediate tactical decisions and complicated strategic considerations, anticipating the eventual impact of taxation on transaction costs and investment decisions.</span><br style=\"line-height: normal; \"><span style=\"line-height: normal; \">&nbsp;</span><br style=\"line-height: normal; \"><span style=\"line-height: normal; \">To retain control, it\'s crucial you have the information that allows you to identify issues in good time and the expert advice that will enable you to factor-in practical measures.</span><br style=\"line-height: normal; \"><span style=\"line-height: normal; \">&nbsp;</span><br style=\"line-height: normal; \"><span style=\"line-height: normal; \">Baker Tilly can help you plan a tax-efficient approach to every aspect of your business, one that sees the whole picture and works with you to protect the interests of your stakeholders.</span><br style=\"line-height: normal; \"><span style=\"line-height: normal; \">&nbsp;</span><br style=\"line-height: normal; \"><span style=\"line-height: normal; \">We look after the interests of corporate entities at every stage of their life- cycle:</span><br style=\"line-height: normal; \"></p><ul style=\"line-height: normal; \"><li style=\"background-image: url(http://www.bakertilly.co.uk/sitecollectionimages/presentation/bullet-black.gif); width: 394.25px; \">start-ups</li><li style=\"background-image: url(http://www.bakertilly.co.uk/sitecollectionimages/presentation/bullet-black.gif); width: 394.25px; \">expansion and investment</li><li style=\"background-image: url(http://www.bakertilly.co.uk/sitecollectionimages/presentation/bullet-black.gif); width: 394.25px; \">acquisitions and disposals</li><li style=\"background-image: url(http://www.bakertilly.co.uk/sitecollectionimages/presentation/bullet-black.gif); width: 394.25px; \">raising finance/capital markets</li><li style=\"background-image: url(http://www.bakertilly.co.uk/sitecollectionimages/presentation/bullet-black.gif); width: 394.25px; \">succession planning.</li></ul><p>We cover all matters related to the compliance, transaction support and planning issues in your sector. Our tax teams have extensive experience in handling all types of communications and negotiations with HM Revenue and Customs (HMRC).</p><h2 class=\"line\" style=\"width: 394.25px; \">Compliance</h2><p><span style=\"line-height: normal; \">HMRC expect you to get your tax right in an environment of complexity, buttressed by a risk-based tax enquiry approach and a penalty regime should you get it wrong. For larger corporates, whether owner managed or part of UK or international groups HMRC require increased visibility into your financial controls which impact on your tax risk and can involve a Client Relationship Manager who has stewardship over your interactions with HMRC on all tax issues.&nbsp;</span><br style=\"line-height: normal; \"><br style=\"line-height: normal; \"><span style=\"line-height: normal; \">Our corporate tax compliance service includes:&nbsp;</span><br style=\"line-height: normal; \"></p><ul style=\"line-height: normal; \"><li style=\"background-image: url(http://www.bakertilly.co.uk/sitecollectionimages/presentation/bullet-black.gif); width: 394.25px; \">Proven approaches and processes for gathering tax data and meeting your financial reporting obligations as regards tax, whether you are an audit client or not.</li><li style=\"background-image: url(http://www.bakertilly.co.uk/sitecollectionimages/presentation/bullet-black.gif); width: 394.25px; \">Preparation and submission of tax computations using the latest software capable of meeting the impending online filing requirements.</li><li style=\"background-image: url(http://www.bakertilly.co.uk/sitecollectionimages/presentation/bullet-black.gif); width: 394.25px; \">Advising on specialist areas such as R&amp;D tax credits, capital allowances on buildings and submitting relevant claims on your behalf.</li><li style=\"background-image: url(http://www.bakertilly.co.uk/sitecollectionimages/presentation/bullet-black.gif); width: 394.25px; \">Agreement of your returns and tax liabilities with HMRC and managing the interface with HMRC on a day to day basis or where you have a formal tax enquiry.</li><li style=\"background-image: url(http://www.bakertilly.co.uk/sitecollectionimages/presentation/bullet-black.gif); width: 394.25px; \">Using the expertise of the firm to quickly resolve HMRC enquiries whether by negotiation using our tax enquiry specialists or technical resource such as our international tax and transfer pricing specialists or technical accounting colleagues.</li></ul><p>Whether an owner managed business or a large group of companies with an international footprint Baker Tilly can devise a tax compliance service to suit your needs; a process designed around accessible people and leading edge technology to ease the ever increasing burden on your business.</p><h2 class=\"line\" style=\"width: 394.25px; \">International tax</h2><p><span style=\"line-height: normal; \">International tax issues can arise for:</span><br style=\"line-height: normal; \"></p><ul style=\"line-height: normal; \"><li style=\"background-image: url(http://www.bakertilly.co.uk/sitecollectionimages/presentation/bullet-black.gif); width: 394.25px; \">UK businesses setting up or expanding overseas</li><li style=\"background-image: url(http://www.bakertilly.co.uk/sitecollectionimages/presentation/bullet-black.gif); width: 394.25px; \">Overseas businesses establishing a presence in the UK.</li></ul><p>Each jurisdiction has its own tax rules and these will interact with UK rules in different ways. Through our international network, Baker Tilly has the knowledge, experience and geographical coverage to provide you with up to date and relevant advice in every territory you are likely to do business in.<br>&nbsp;<br>After gaining an understanding of your business and aims for expanding into new markets, Baker Tilly will be in a position to develop a tax structure that:</p><ul style=\"line-height: normal; \"><li style=\"background-image: url(http://www.bakertilly.co.uk/sitecollectionimages/presentation/bullet-black.gif); width: 394.25px; \">is appropriate to your needs (with particular regard to added complexity versus benefit); and</li><li style=\"background-image: url(http://www.bakertilly.co.uk/sitecollectionimages/presentation/bullet-black.gif); width: 394.25px; \">minimises the group\'s overall tax liability.</li></ul><p>In addition, we are well versed in managing the increased compliance burden that result from overseas expansion.</p>', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', ''),
(113, 'en', 1, 70, 1, NULL, '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', 1, '', 0, 0, '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', 'Employer consulting services', '<h2>Our Aim</h2><p>Our aim is to help employers attract, retain and motivate employees, while controlling employment costs and risks against a background of increasing payroll taxes and constantly evolving regulatory burdens.&nbsp;</p><h2>How we can help</h2><p>You may need quick, practical advice on questions as they arise in your day to day work, and need someone who can be relied on to keep you up to date with changes in law and practice&nbsp;<strong>which affect you as an employer</strong>. You may from time to time need more extensive help in any of the areas outlined below.</p><h2>Employee Remuneration &amp; Strategy</h2><p>We can help design a remuneration strategy to attract, retain and motivate the right people, and where appropriate implement share plans, bonus plans and other forms of remuneration to support your business strategy.</p><h2>Internal Policies and Procedures</h2><p>We help employers in writing or reviewing policies on areas including pay, benefits and expenses, termination payments, engagement of consultants and construction industry subcontractors. We take into account the tax and NIC and other regulatory rules, and the experience of many other clients in formulating policy in this area. We also help to minimise tax reporting obligations by managing P11D dispensations and PAYE settlement agreements with HM Revenue &amp; Customs.&nbsp;</p><h2>PAYE visits from HM Revenue &amp; Customs</h2><p>We help clients at all stages of enquiry visits by HMRC to check PAYE/NIC compliance including preparation for a review, conduct during it and negotiating settlements where claims for tax arise.</p><h2>Expatriate Employees to &amp; from the UK</h2><p>We provide a range of services to help employers deal with international assignments, including helping to structure assignments as tax efficiently as possible and to cater for the complexity of exposure to more than one tax regime, guiding assignees on their obligations, assisting with their personal tax compliance in the home and host countries and liaising with HMRC on behalf of the employer and the assignee.</p>', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', ''),
(114, 'en', 1, 71, 1, NULL, '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', 1, '', 0, 0, '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', 'Services to private clients', '<p><font class=\"intro\" style=\"line-height: normal; \">Protecting family wealth is a priority for most people, and effective tax planning has a large part to play in this process.</font><span style=\"line-height: normal; \">&nbsp;</span><br style=\"line-height: normal; \"><br style=\"line-height: normal; \"><span style=\"line-height: normal; \">Our experts can advise you on every aspect of your personal tax position, from dealing with your annual self assessment Tax Return to advising on capital gains tax, wills and inheritance tax planning.</span><br style=\"line-height: normal; \"><span style=\"line-height: normal; \">A thorough understanding of your needs, objectives and plans for the future is at the very centre of this advice.</span><br style=\"line-height: normal; \"><span style=\"line-height: normal; \">&nbsp;</span><br style=\"line-height: normal; \"><span style=\"line-height: normal; \">Drawing on our experience we will examine issues that you may not have considered, ensuring that your wealth is working effectively for you and that you are planning for both the expected and the unexpected.</span><br style=\"line-height: normal; \"><span style=\"line-height: normal; \">&nbsp;</span><br style=\"line-height: normal; \"><span style=\"line-height: normal; \">Flexibility is key: what works today may not be appropriate in five or ten years\' time. We will keep your tax planning strategy under review so that it can be adapted to suit your changing circumstances, or in response to ever-changing tax legislation.</span><br style=\"line-height: normal; \"><span style=\"line-height: normal; \">&nbsp;</span><br style=\"line-height: normal; \"><span style=\"line-height: normal; \">Our services to private clients include:</span><br style=\"line-height: normal; \"><br></p><ul style=\"line-height: normal; \"><li style=\"background-image: url(http://www.bakertilly.co.uk/sitecollectionimages/presentation/bullet-black.gif); width: 394.25px; \">completion of your self assessment Tax Return</li><li style=\"background-image: url(http://www.bakertilly.co.uk/sitecollectionimages/presentation/bullet-black.gif); width: 394.25px; \">capital gains tax planning</li><li style=\"background-image: url(http://www.bakertilly.co.uk/sitecollectionimages/presentation/bullet-black.gif); width: 394.25px; \">inheritance tax planning and advice on wills</li><li style=\"background-image: url(http://www.bakertilly.co.uk/sitecollectionimages/presentation/bullet-black.gif); width: 394.25px; \">exit and succession planning</li><li style=\"background-image: url(http://www.bakertilly.co.uk/sitecollectionimages/presentation/bullet-black.gif); width: 394.25px; \">services for non-domiciled and expatriate clients</li><li style=\"background-image: url(http://www.bakertilly.co.uk/sitecollectionimages/presentation/bullet-black.gif); width: 394.25px; \">wealth management services</li><li style=\"background-image: url(http://www.bakertilly.co.uk/sitecollectionimages/presentation/bullet-black.gif); width: 394.25px; \">trust accounting and tax compliance</li><li style=\"background-image: url(http://www.bakertilly.co.uk/sitecollectionimages/presentation/bullet-black.gif); width: 394.25px; \">administration of estates.</li></ul><p><span style=\"line-height: normal; \">Whether your financial affairs are straightforward or highly complex you will have a dedicated specialist allocated to you. We develop long-term relationships with our clients in order to deliver a service which meets your specific needs. Whether you require ongoing services or one off specialist advice we will be happy to quote and provide a full explanation of our fees, assisting in your decision to go ahead.</span></p>', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', ''),
(115, 'en', 1, 72, 1, NULL, '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', 1, '', 0, 0, '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', 'Tax risk and investigation management services', '<p class=\"intro\">An investigation by HM Revenue &amp; Customs (HMRC) can be very disruptive and expensive: that\'s why we strive to resolve matters quickly and secure the best results for individuals and businesses. We successfully resolve disputes day in and day out because we know how the taxman thinks.</p><p>Our team of tax investigation specialists understands&nbsp;the stress and anxiety investigations can cause. Our team, short-listed in 2007 and 2008 and then winners of \'Best Tax Investigations Team\' at the prestigious&nbsp;<a data-cke-saved-href=\"http://www.bakertilly.co.uk/media/news/Lexis-Nexis-Taxation-Awards-Tax-Investigations.aspx\" href=\"http://www.bakertilly.co.uk/media/news/Lexis-Nexis-Taxation-Awards-Tax-Investigations.aspx\">2009 Taxation Awards</a>, has spent years working at a senior level at HMRC or settling enquiries with tax authorities.</p><p>Understanding the tax inspector allows us to predict HMRC’s actions and respond to them effectively. Our expertise allows us to develop a strategy to maintain control of an enquiry and shape the most cost-effective outcome for you. We tailor our services to meet your unique needs and can tackle all types of investigations or enquiries. We can handle the investigation for you directly or provide a specialist support service to your other advisers, including your legal team.</p>', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', ''),
(116, 'en', 1, 73, 1, NULL, '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', 1, '', 0, 0, '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', 'VAT and indirect tax', '<p class=\"intro\">The issues and questions surrounding VAT are notoriously difficult and, with increased legislation and regulation, this makes VAT one of the most complex taxes encountered.</p><p>Your VAT needs may range from routine compliance to specialist advice, but, no matter the complexities of your organization, Baker Tilly’s VAT team can support your business strategies and provide expert advice to manage your tax liabilities and costs.<br><br>No matter which particular business sector or particular business circumstance you are in, you will receive practical, commercial advice specific to your business needs.</p><p>Baker Tilly’s VAT team can help you plan a VAT efficient approach to every aspect of your business. Whether that be:</p><ul style=\"line-height: normal; \"><li style=\"background-image: url(http://www.bakertilly.co.uk/sitecollectionimages/presentation/bullet-black.gif); width: 394.25px; \">VAT consulting and compliance services for cross-border or UK supplies of goods and services</li><li style=\"background-image: url(http://www.bakertilly.co.uk/sitecollectionimages/presentation/bullet-black.gif); width: 394.25px; \">Capital and revenue spending reviews</li><li style=\"background-image: url(http://www.bakertilly.co.uk/sitecollectionimages/presentation/bullet-black.gif); width: 394.25px; \">VAT advice on proposed transactions or</li><li style=\"background-image: url(http://www.bakertilly.co.uk/sitecollectionimages/presentation/bullet-black.gif); width: 394.25px; \">VAT healthchecks</li></ul><p>We cover all matters related to the compliance, transaction support and planning issues to enable your organization to enhance cashflow and minimize risk.</p><p>Baker Tilly’s team of VAT experts will assist you in implementing your VAT strategy, assist you with enhancing the efficiency and effectiveness of your in-house tax and VAT functions, help mitigate any transgressions and penalties through our innovative solutions, negotiate with fiscal authorities through any enquiry or investigation and provide bespoke training for your key personnel.<br><br>Whether your VAT affairs are straightforward or highly complex, whether you require one off specialist advice or ongoing services, you will benefit from VAT expert working with you to achieve your aims.</p>', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', ''),
(117, 'en', 1, 74, 1, NULL, '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', 1, '', 0, 0, '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', 'null', '<p>Today Azerbaijan aims to remove dependence of economy on oil and natural resources and assure expansion of economic development to rural areas. Baker Tilly Azerbaijan has the expertise to support farmers, landowners, agri-businesses and allied industries. <br></p><p>Our team can support you in bellow matters:<br></p><ul><li> Restructuring Existing business<br></li><li> Reorganizing Finances<br></li><li> Identifying new uses for old assets <br></li><li>Entering new markets <br></li><li>Learning additional skills <br></li><li>Working with environmental issues <br></li></ul><p>Through our practical experience in agriculture, we can provide you with personal guidance and support, helping you to achieve defined goals and objectives.<br></p>', 'null', 'null', 'null', 'null', 'null', 'null', 'null', 'null', 'null', 'null', 'null', 'null', 'null', 'null', 'null', 'null', 'null', 'null', 'null', 'null', 'null', 'null', 'null', 'null', 'null', 'null', 'null', 'null', 'null', 'null', 'null', 'null', 'null', 'null', 'null', 'null', 'null', 'null'),
(118, 'en', 1, 75, 1, NULL, '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', 1, '', 0, 0, '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', 'null', '<p>Automotive sector is highly interesting and demanded in Azerbaijan even during the Soviet Union period. In today’s business environment manufacturers require larger volumes and higher retail standards, the motor sector is under ever-increasing competition. <br></p><p>Now, customers have more choice, new manufacturers breaking into the market and an increasing use of the internet for research. <br></p><p>Our expert support can help you improve your profits by reviewing your business strategy and managing risk more effectively.<br></p>', 'null', 'null', 'null', 'null', 'null', 'null', 'null', 'null', 'null', 'null', 'null', 'null', 'null', 'null', 'null', 'null', 'null', 'null', 'null', 'null', 'null', 'null', 'null', 'null', 'null', 'null', 'null', 'null', 'null', 'null', 'null', 'null', 'null', 'null', 'null', 'null', 'null', 'null'),
(119, 'en', 1, 76, 1, NULL, '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', 1, '', 0, 0, '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', 'Business services', '<p class=\"intro\">The current recessionary economic environment is a double edged sword for the business services sector.</p><p>In an age of austerity, cost control is an area of focus for all businesses.&nbsp;With revenue growth difficult to achieve, there is a real drive in both the public and private sector to ensure maximum efficiency in all areas of back office (i.e. administrative) and indeed even some front office (client facing) services.&nbsp;This is leading to pressure to consider outsourcing all but essential, core business functions in areas such as:</p><ul style=\"line-height: normal; \"><li style=\"background-image: url(http://www.bakertilly.co.uk/sitecollectionimages/presentation/bullet-black.gif); width: 394.25px; \">Recruitment</li><li style=\"background-image: url(http://www.bakertilly.co.uk/sitecollectionimages/presentation/bullet-black.gif); width: 394.25px; \">IT</li><li style=\"background-image: url(http://www.bakertilly.co.uk/sitecollectionimages/presentation/bullet-black.gif); width: 394.25px; \">Cleaning &amp; waste management</li><li style=\"background-image: url(http://www.bakertilly.co.uk/sitecollectionimages/presentation/bullet-black.gif); width: 394.25px; \">Facilities management</li><li style=\"background-image: url(http://www.bakertilly.co.uk/sitecollectionimages/presentation/bullet-black.gif); width: 394.25px; \">Order processing &amp; invoicing</li></ul><p><strong>Helping our clients with current sector issues</strong><br><br>However, where services are already outsourced, cost constraints are forcing retendering and other attempts to drive down costs. Some of these are bold; outright attempts to reduce contractually agreed terms, are no longer shocking and are almost expected.&nbsp;The key is to know what concessions can be extracted in return to mitigate the pain. Even though the full impact of public sector cuts may result in reductions in the purchase of some services, in many cases restructuring of contracts over longer periods may serve to lengthen the period over which reliable cash flows can be predicted.</p><p>There are other opportunities. Despite the best efforts of the coalition to curtail regulation, they are likely to have limited success.&nbsp;The ever onward march of regulation in areas such as employment rights, health and safety and environmental laws is leading to greater reliance on third party suppliers.</p><p><strong>Industry expertise with international reach</strong><br><br>In challenging times, we understand the issues the business service sector faces.&nbsp;We have an integrated approach across different geographies and disciplines designed to deliver the highest quality advice in the most efficient way.&nbsp;Throughout the UK and internationally, Baker Tilly will harness its network of experts to deliver strong, local support across a range of disciplines including:</p><ul style=\"line-height: normal; \"><li style=\"background-image: url(http://www.bakertilly.co.uk/sitecollectionimages/presentation/bullet-black.gif); width: 394.25px; \"><a data-cke-saved-href=\"http://www.bakertilly.co.uk/services/audit/audit.aspx\" href=\"http://www.bakertilly.co.uk/services/audit/audit.aspx\">Audit and assurance services</a></li><li style=\"background-image: url(http://www.bakertilly.co.uk/sitecollectionimages/presentation/bullet-black.gif); width: 394.25px; \"><a data-cke-saved-href=\"http://www.bakertilly.co.uk/services/tax/tax.aspx\" href=\"http://www.bakertilly.co.uk/services/tax/tax.aspx\">Tax advice and compliance</a>&nbsp;with corporation tax and VAT</li><li style=\"background-image: url(http://www.bakertilly.co.uk/sitecollectionimages/presentation/bullet-black.gif); width: 394.25px; \"><a data-cke-saved-href=\"http://www.bakertilly.co.uk/services/finance/corporate-finance.aspx\" href=\"http://www.bakertilly.co.uk/services/finance/corporate-finance.aspx\">Corporate finance advice</a>&nbsp;on strategic acquisitions, exit plans, business disposals, initial public offerings and debt and equity fund raising</li><li style=\"background-image: url(http://www.bakertilly.co.uk/sitecollectionimages/presentation/bullet-black.gif); width: 394.25px; \"><a data-cke-saved-href=\"http://www.bakertilly.co.uk/services/tax/employer-consulting-services.aspx\" href=\"http://www.bakertilly.co.uk/services/tax/employer-consulting-services.aspx\">Remuneration planning</a>&nbsp;including tax efficient incentive schemes</li></ul>', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', ''),
(120, 'en', 1, 77, 1, NULL, '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', 1, '', 0, 0, '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', 'Recruitment', '<h2>At Baker Tilly we thoroughly enjoy working with professionals from across the recruitment sector and we believe that the entrepreneurial spirit that drives this market will play a crucial role in helping the UK economy to restore growth. The Recruitment market provides labour flexibility for all and ensures businesses can access the talent they need.</h2><p>The range of businesses making up the recruitment sector is indeed vast. From small start-ups to listed multinationals, contingent temporary and permanent providers to global executive search houses, each type of recruitment business is subject to its own specific needs.</p><p>At Baker Tilly, we have worked will all types of organisations and our experience has been developed over many years.&nbsp; We focus on the people behind the businesses we act for as well as the businesses themselves, meaning we understand what it is like to be you.&nbsp; Only in this way can we truly help you to realise the strategic ambitions you have for your organisation.</p><p><strong>The key issues we see recruitment businesses facing include</strong>:</p><ul style=\"line-height: normal; \"><li style=\"background-image: url(http://www.bakertilly.co.uk/sitecollectionimages/presentation/bullet-black.gif); width: 394.25px; \">Attracting, retaining and rewarding high calibre consultants</li><li style=\"background-image: url(http://www.bakertilly.co.uk/sitecollectionimages/presentation/bullet-black.gif); width: 394.25px; \">Sourcing quality candidates</li><li style=\"background-image: url(http://www.bakertilly.co.uk/sitecollectionimages/presentation/bullet-black.gif); width: 394.25px; \">Managing relationships with your clients</li><li style=\"background-image: url(http://www.bakertilly.co.uk/sitecollectionimages/presentation/bullet-black.gif); width: 394.25px; \">Expansion into new domestic or overseas markets</li><li style=\"background-image: url(http://www.bakertilly.co.uk/sitecollectionimages/presentation/bullet-black.gif); width: 394.25px; \">Operating your business efficiently</li><li style=\"background-image: url(http://www.bakertilly.co.uk/sitecollectionimages/presentation/bullet-black.gif); width: 394.25px; \">Consistent revenue performance</li></ul><p><strong>The services our recruitment sector clients most seek from us include the following</strong>:</p><ul style=\"line-height: normal; \"><li style=\"background-image: url(http://www.bakertilly.co.uk/sitecollectionimages/presentation/bullet-black.gif); width: 394.25px; \">Share ownership and share options advice</li><li style=\"background-image: url(http://www.bakertilly.co.uk/sitecollectionimages/presentation/bullet-black.gif); width: 394.25px; \">Use of company and limited liability partnership hybrid structures</li><li style=\"background-image: url(http://www.bakertilly.co.uk/sitecollectionimages/presentation/bullet-black.gif); width: 394.25px; \">Corporate finance advice on buying and selling your business</li><li style=\"background-image: url(http://www.bakertilly.co.uk/sitecollectionimages/presentation/bullet-black.gif); width: 394.25px; \">PAYE advice</li><li style=\"background-image: url(http://www.bakertilly.co.uk/sitecollectionimages/presentation/bullet-black.gif); width: 394.25px; \">Web based back office solutions specifically developed for the sector<ul><li style=\"background-image: url(http://www.bakertilly.co.uk/sitecollectionimages/presentation/bullet-black.gif); width: 394.25px; \">InTime - pay and bill solution</li><li style=\"background-image: url(http://www.bakertilly.co.uk/sitecollectionimages/presentation/bullet-black.gif); width: 394.25px; \">SaaS accounting solution</li></ul></li><li style=\"background-image: url(http://www.bakertilly.co.uk/sitecollectionimages/presentation/bullet-black.gif); width: 394.25px; \">Outsourcing<ul><li style=\"background-image: url(http://www.bakertilly.co.uk/sitecollectionimages/presentation/bullet-black.gif); width: 394.25px; \">Payroll and billing</li><li style=\"background-image: url(http://www.bakertilly.co.uk/sitecollectionimages/presentation/bullet-black.gif); width: 394.25px; \">Accounting</li></ul></li><li style=\"background-image: url(http://www.bakertilly.co.uk/sitecollectionimages/presentation/bullet-black.gif); width: 394.25px; \">Audit</li><li style=\"background-image: url(http://www.bakertilly.co.uk/sitecollectionimages/presentation/bullet-black.gif); width: 394.25px; \">Tax compliance</li><li style=\"background-image: url(http://www.bakertilly.co.uk/sitecollectionimages/presentation/bullet-black.gif); width: 394.25px; \">Revenue performance management</li></ul><p>Our Recruitment sector team would be delighted to share their market insights with you and help support you to achieve your business objectives.&nbsp;&nbsp; Please do give us a call or send us an email – we’d love to hear from you.</p>', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', ''),
(121, 'en', 1, 78, 1, NULL, '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', 1, '', 0, 0, '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', 'null', '<p>Azerbaijan is gifted in terms of having rich energy and natural resources. Country’s current economic development players are mainly oil and gas sector. Local and International companies in the country deal with exploring oil and gas fields, producing, processing, and transporting oil, gas, and gas condensate, marketing petroleum and petrochemical products in domestic and international markets, and supplying natural gas to industry and the public in Azerbaijan.<br></p><p> Baker Tilly Azerbaijan has wide experience of working with clients in the energy and natural resources sector: <br></p><ul><li>Oil and gas exploration and production <br></li><li>Mineral extraction<br></li><li> Renewables and clean technologies <br></li></ul><p>In this sector we provide support and expertise and add value in areas such as: <br></p><ul><li>Accounting and audit requirements of operating in overseas jurisdictions <br></li><li>Best practices in the energy, natural resources and renewable sectors <br></li><li>Early warning of key issues and changes to regulation, tax and compliance standards <br></li><li>Forensic accounting requirements <br></li><li>Profit sharing agreements<br></li><li> Royalty audits and royalty agreement reviews <br></li><li>Tax and financial due diligence for mergers and acquisitions transactions <br></li><li>Tax efficient means of retaining and rewarding key staff and directors<br></li></ul>', 'null', 'null', 'null', 'null', 'null', 'null', 'null', 'null', 'null', 'null', 'null', 'null', 'null', 'null', 'null', 'null', 'null', 'null', 'null', 'null', 'null', 'null', 'null', 'null', 'null', 'null', 'null', 'null', 'null', 'null', 'null', 'null', 'null', 'null', 'null', 'null', 'null', 'null'),
(122, 'en', 1, 79, 1, NULL, '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', 1, '', 0, 0, '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', 'Oil and gas exploration and production', '<p>Oil and Gas continue to account for more than half of global energy consumption.&nbsp; No other industry seems to illustrate as vividly the complex interplay between the ever-increasing demand from population growth and industrialisation of developing regions and the pressures on supply from worldwide events like the Arab Spring, the Japanese Tsunami and the BP Gulf of Mexico disaster.&nbsp;The sector is also impacted by the potential for the ‘technological fix’ offered by new non-conventional resources such as shale gas and the moral and environmental pressures to seek cleaner alternative energy sources.&nbsp;</p><p>But Oil and Gas is not all about global events and the headline-making ‘super-majors’.&nbsp;The industry employs a vast number of people and supports companies both large and small, across a range of sectors, from start-up explorers in frontier regions to large scale producers in established fields, from specialised engineering and technology consultancy to the garage forecourt.&nbsp;</p><p>Despite the challenges of the current global economy, the general mood amongst our Oil and Gas clients is positive.&nbsp;The long term economic fundamentals remain strong and there is still no immediate threat to market share from alternative energy sources.&nbsp;The long term nature of investment in Oil and Gas limits the impact of short or medium term shocks and companies in the sector believe that funding and profit will continue to be accessible for the right projects and the right companies.</p><h3>Practical and relevant solutions to help your business succeed</h3><p><strong>We can help to identify and address your principal areas of interest and concern including:</strong></p><ul style=\"line-height: normal; \"><li style=\"background-image: url(http://www.bakertilly.co.uk/sitecollectionimages/presentation/bullet-black.gif); width: 394.25px; \">Complying with the UK Bribery Act by a review and implementation of appropriate systems</li><li style=\"background-image: url(http://www.bakertilly.co.uk/sitecollectionimages/presentation/bullet-black.gif); width: 394.25px; \">Understanding the necessary board procedures and how best practice corporate governance can work for the natural resources sector</li><li style=\"background-image: url(http://www.bakertilly.co.uk/sitecollectionimages/presentation/bullet-black.gif); width: 394.25px; \">Practical experience of Capital Markets transactions and an understanding of the technical requirements involved, including liaison with competent persons and other specialists</li><li style=\"background-image: url(http://www.bakertilly.co.uk/sitecollectionimages/presentation/bullet-black.gif); width: 394.25px; \">Indentifying the most efficient Corporate Tax structure for a global resources group</li><li style=\"background-image: url(http://www.bakertilly.co.uk/sitecollectionimages/presentation/bullet-black.gif); width: 394.25px; \">How to ensure the operation of good financial controls when dealing with remote operational locations</li></ul><h3>Contact us</h3><p>We have a team dedicated to providing advice and services to a range of business within the Oil and Gas sector. Our expertise involves working with privately owned businesses, private equity backed and quoted businesses both within the UK and internationally. Our sector experience, combined with a committed and experienced team enables us to work closely with our clients helping them to achieve their strategic goals.</p><p>If you would like to have a confidential discussion on your strategic growth plans, your compliance and / or advisory requirements please contact&nbsp;<a data-cke-saved-href=\"http://www.bakertilly.co.uk/contact/people/Pages/Paul-Watts.aspx\" href=\"http://www.bakertilly.co.uk/contact/people/Pages/Paul-Watts.aspx\">Paul Watts</a>, Head of Energy and Natural Resources for Baker Tilly.</p>', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', ''),
(123, 'en', 1, 80, 1, NULL, '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', 1, '', 0, 0, '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', 'Mining and metals', '<p>The Mining and Metals sector has an attractive long term future but is facing new challenges in the short term. The perennial problem facing the sector is matching the short and long term pressures of supply and demand so that there is a fair balance between the owners, the explorers and producers and the end users of the world’s finite mineral resources. This results in a highly competitive and cyclical environment in which companies in the sector operate. Whilst dominated by major global players, there is a significant role to play for the junior Mining companies who identify and explore assets at the margins and at early stages creating significant investor opportunities as well as then facing the decision whether to sell to larger players or develop their mining assets themselves as a strategic play.</p><p>The prospects for the global economy are challenging with weakening demand from China, Europe and Western economies and the knock on effect on commodity prices, but this needs to be balanced against the mid to longer term pressures of security of supply of key resources and strong growth forecasts for developing economies over the next decade. Those countries that are resource rich, particularly those in Africa, are looking to retain more of the benefits from the industry beyond royalty and tax take and are expecting to retain a greater equity share of their Mining and Metals industries, whilst recognising that they still need the technical knowhow and demand from foreign investors to properly exploit the resources. Mining and Metals companies bravely face these continued challenges together with increased environmental concerns, skilled labour shortages and political risk, but the sector as a whole remains attractive to investors and companies alike.</p><h3>Practical and relevant solutions to help your business succeed</h3><p><strong>We can help to identify and address your principal areas of interest and concern including:</strong></p><ul style=\"line-height: normal; \"><li style=\"background-image: url(http://www.bakertilly.co.uk/sitecollectionimages/presentation/bullet-black.gif); width: 394.25px; \">Complying with the UK Bribery Act by a review and implementation of appropriate systems</li><li style=\"background-image: url(http://www.bakertilly.co.uk/sitecollectionimages/presentation/bullet-black.gif); width: 394.25px; \">Understanding the necessary board procedures and how best practice corporate governance can work for the natural resources sector</li><li style=\"background-image: url(http://www.bakertilly.co.uk/sitecollectionimages/presentation/bullet-black.gif); width: 394.25px; \">Practical experience of Capital Markets transactions and an understanding of the technical requirements involved, including liaison with competent persons and other specialists</li><li style=\"background-image: url(http://www.bakertilly.co.uk/sitecollectionimages/presentation/bullet-black.gif); width: 394.25px; \">Indentifying the most efficient Corporate Tax structure for a global resources group</li><li style=\"background-image: url(http://www.bakertilly.co.uk/sitecollectionimages/presentation/bullet-black.gif); width: 394.25px; \">How to ensure the operation of good financial controls when dealing with remote operational locations.</li></ul><h3>Contact us</h3><p>We have a team dedicated to providing advice and services to a range of business within the Mining and Metals sector. Our expertise involves working with privately owned businesses, private equity backed and quoted businesses both within the UK and internationally. Our sector experience, combined with a committed and experienced team enables us to work closely with our clients helping them to achieve their strategic goals.</p><p>If you would like to have a confidential discussion on your strategic growth plans, your compliance and / or advisory requirements please contact&nbsp;<a data-cke-saved-href=\"http://www.bakertilly.co.uk/contact/people/Pages/Paul-Watts.aspx\" href=\"http://www.bakertilly.co.uk/contact/people/Pages/Paul-Watts.aspx\">Paul Watts</a>, Head of Energy and Natural Resources for Baker Tilly.</p>', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', ''),
(124, 'en', 1, 81, 1, NULL, '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', 1, '', 0, 0, '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', 'Renewables and cleantech', '<p>The renewable energy and cleantech technology sector has many attractive qualities for investors and debt providers as countries around the World seek to reduce their dependency on energy imports and particularly oil and gas sources. In the UK market, the Climate Change Act dictates that renewable energy sources are required to supply 20% of total energy by 2020 which is estimated to require the current rate of investment to double to meet these challenges.&nbsp; Furthermore, with many countries agreeing that there also needs to be wide scale reductions in global carbon emissions, many Governments are looking at initiatives to increase the cost of emissions and make alternative energy sources more attractive and financially viable. To do so, it is increasingly important that the sector provides a stable environment for potential investors with a degree of certainty over future Government initiatives and support regimes.</p><p>In economy terms, the need for Countries to reduce their carbon emissions in the long term and fulfil their energy demands will likely underpin this sector in the medium to long term.&nbsp; However, regularly changing Government initiatives and the economic downturn in Europe and the US has affected short term performance in the sector and increased volatility and uncertainty.&nbsp; Although the above have been factors across the sector as a whole, the impact has varied between companies depending on the stage in their life cycle and also the specific type of renewable energy / technologies involved.</p><h3>Practical and relevant solutions to help your business succeed</h3><p><strong>We can help to identify and address your principal areas of inters and concern including:</strong></p><ul style=\"line-height: normal; \"><li style=\"background-image: url(http://www.bakertilly.co.uk/sitecollectionimages/presentation/bullet-black.gif); width: 394.25px; \">Tax advisory and structuring advice including international tax structuring advice, advice on best corporate structuring vehicles, specialist advice on EIS/VCT eligibility, R &amp; D optimisation and maximising capital allowances;</li><li style=\"background-image: url(http://www.bakertilly.co.uk/sitecollectionimages/presentation/bullet-black.gif); width: 394.25px; \">Practical experience of Capital Markets transactions and an understanding of the technical requirements involved, including liaison with specialists;</li><li style=\"background-image: url(http://www.bakertilly.co.uk/sitecollectionimages/presentation/bullet-black.gif); width: 394.25px; \">Highly experienced funder due diligence team who have advised on over 20 transactions with a combined value in excess of £260m;</li><li style=\"background-image: url(http://www.bakertilly.co.uk/sitecollectionimages/presentation/bullet-black.gif); width: 394.25px; \">Specialist financial modelling team who have significant experience preparing financial models for business plan purposes or specific funding requirements including senior personnel who have carried out secondments at the Department of Energy and Climate Change.</li></ul><h3>Contact us</h3><p>We have a team dedicated to providing advice and services to a range of business within the Renewables and Cleantech sector. Our expertise involves working with privately owned businesses, private equity backed and quoted businesses both within the UK and internationally. Our sector experience, combined with a committed and experienced team enables us to work closely with our clients helping them to achieve their strategic goals.&nbsp;<br><br>If you would like to have a confidential discussion on your strategic growth plans, your compliance and / or advisory requirements please contact&nbsp;<a data-cke-saved-href=\"http://www.bakertilly.co.uk/contact/people/Pages/Diane-Gwilliam.aspx\" href=\"http://www.bakertilly.co.uk/contact/people/Pages/Diane-Gwilliam.aspx\">Diane Gwilliam</a>, Head of Renewables and Cleantech for Baker Tilly.</p>', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', ''),
(125, 'en', 1, 82, 1, NULL, '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', 1, '', 0, 0, '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', 'null', '<p>The financial industry is a highly regulated one and those who wish to operate within this sector have an increasingly complex day to day business environment to deal with. The future will be equally challenging with continuing regulatory developments. <br></p><p>We have a team of experts who specialize in financial services and have a deep knowledge of the issues facing businesses in this environment and understand the challenges faced by financial services’ regulated entities and provide a joined-up, partner led service to our clients. <br></p><p>We advise on a full range of business matters, from statutory audit, corporation tax and VAT planning and compliance and corporate finance advice through to risk management and financial services compliance matters. Our team of experts provides practical and commercial solutions to your problems.<br></p><p> In addition to compliance services such as audit and corporation tax, we also provide specialist advisory support, particularly relevant to the financial services sector. This ranges from areas such as risk management control, through to internal audit and monitoring procedures. At all times we work closely with our clients at Board and Shareholder level, helping to identify their business needs, and providing a suitably tailored service based on their requirements.<br></p>', 'null', 'null', 'null', 'null', 'null', 'null', 'null', 'null', 'null', 'null', 'null', 'null', 'null', 'null', 'null', 'null', 'null', 'null', 'null', 'null', 'null', 'null', 'null', 'null', 'null', 'null', 'null', 'null', 'null', 'null', 'null', 'null', 'null', 'null', 'null', 'null', 'null', 'null');
