(14, 'Optare', 'Optare', '<p><span style=\"font-family: arial, sans-serif; font-size: 12px; line-height: normal; \">Baker Tilly are proud to announce their part in the North West Insider Magazine&#39;s AIM transaction of the year. The North Region Corporate Finance team acted as advisor and reporting accountant to Darwen Holdings Limited.</span><br style=\"font-family: arial, sans-serif; font-size: 12px; line-height: normal; \" />\n<span style=\"font-family: arial, sans-serif; font-size: 12px; line-height: normal; \">&nbsp;</span><br style=\"font-family: arial, sans-serif; font-size: 12px; line-height: normal; \" />\n<span style=\"font-family: arial, sans-serif; font-size: 12px; line-height: normal; \">In 2008 Darwen was admitted to AIM, having previously acquired the business of East Lancashire Coachbuilders Ltd, builders of double deck buses. The original acquisition had been funded by a private placing. Following this transaction, Darwen acquired Optare Group Ltd, builders of a range of single deck buses and coaches. A reverse acquisition, &pound;16million of new capital was raised and on readmission, the group was renamed Optare plc.</span><br style=\"font-family: arial, sans-serif; font-size: 12px; line-height: normal; \" />\n<span style=\"font-family: arial, sans-serif; font-size: 12px; line-height: normal; \">&nbsp;</span><br style=\"font-family: arial, sans-serif; font-size: 12px; line-height: normal; \" />\n<span style=\"font-family: arial, sans-serif; font-size: 12px; line-height: normal; \">With an estimated turnover of &pound;90million, Optare is now considered to be the second largest bus builder in the UK. The group offers a comprehensive range of vehicles, covering the complete spectrum of bus and coach operation, tailored to the individual needs of the customers.</span><br style=\"font-family: arial, sans-serif; font-size: 12px; line-height: normal; \" />\n<span style=\"font-family: arial, sans-serif; font-size: 12px; line-height: normal; \">&nbsp;</span><br style=\"font-family: arial, sans-serif; font-size: 12px; line-height: normal; \" />\n<em style=\"font-family: arial, sans-serif; font-size: 12px; line-height: normal; \">&quot;Baker Tilly advised on all aspects of the transaction involved in creating the group, including a key role in our placing and admission to AIM. Their effective and focussed approach was essential to the IPO, and subsequent readmission. A complex set of transactions that were carried out in a tight timetable.&quot;</em><br style=\"font-family: arial, sans-serif; font-size: 12px; line-height: normal; \" />\n<strong style=\"font-family: arial, sans-serif; font-size: 12px; line-height: normal; \">Mike Dunn, Chief Financial Officer, Optare plc</strong></p>\n', '<p><span style=\"font-family: arial, sans-serif; font-size: 12px; line-height: normal; \">Baker Tilly are proud to announce their part in the North West Insider Magazine&#39;s AIM transaction of the year. The North Region Corporate Finance team acted as advisor and reporting accountant to Darwen Holdings Limited.</span><br style=\"font-family: arial, sans-serif; font-size: 12px; line-height: normal; \" />\n<span style=\"font-family: arial, sans-serif; font-size: 12px; line-height: normal; \">&nbsp;</span><br style=\"font-family: arial, sans-serif; font-size: 12px; line-height: normal; \" />\n<span style=\"font-family: arial, sans-serif; font-size: 12px; line-height: normal; \">In 2008 Darwen was admitted to AIM, having previously acquired the business of East Lancashire Coachbuilders Ltd, builders of double deck buses. The original acquisition had been funded by a private placing. Following this transaction, Darwen acquired Optare Group Ltd, builders of a range of single deck buses and coaches. A reverse acquisition, &pound;16million of new capital was raised and on readmission, the group was renamed Optare plc.</span><br style=\"font-family: arial, sans-serif; font-size: 12px; line-height: normal; \" />\n<span style=\"font-family: arial, sans-serif; font-size: 12px; line-height: normal; \">&nbsp;</span><br style=\"font-family: arial, sans-serif; font-size: 12px; line-height: normal; \" />\n<span style=\"font-family: arial, sans-serif; font-size: 12px; line-height: normal; \">With an estimated turnover of &pound;90million, Optare is now considered to be the second largest bus builder in the UK. The group offers a comprehensive range of vehicles, covering the complete spectrum of bus and coach operation, tailored to the individual needs of the customers.</span><br style=\"font-family: arial, sans-serif; font-size: 12px; line-height: normal; \" />\n<span style=\"font-family: arial, sans-serif; font-size: 12px; line-height: normal; \">&nbsp;</span><br style=\"font-family: arial, sans-serif; font-size: 12px; line-height: normal; \" />\n<em style=\"font-family: arial, sans-serif; font-size: 12px; line-height: normal; \">&quot;Baker Tilly advised on all aspects of the transaction involved in creating the group, including a key role in our placing and admission to AIM. Their effective and focussed approach was essential to the IPO, and subsequent readmission. A complex set of transactions that were carried out in a tight timetable.&quot;</em><br style=\"font-family: arial, sans-serif; font-size: 12px; line-height: normal; \" />\n<strong style=\"font-family: arial, sans-serif; font-size: 12px; line-height: normal; \">Mike Dunn, Chief Financial Officer, Optare plc</strong></p>\n', '<p><span style=\"font-family: arial, sans-serif; font-size: 12px; line-height: 15px; \">Baker Tilly are proud to announce their part in the North West Insider Magazine&#39;s AIM transaction of the year. The North Region Corporate Finance team acted as advisor and reporting accountant to Darwen Holdings Limited.</span></p>\n', '<p><span style=\"font-family: arial, sans-serif; font-size: 12px; line-height: 15px; \">Baker Tilly are proud to announce their part in the North West Insider Magazine&#39;s AIM transaction of the year