(15, 'St Anthony\'s', 'St Anthony\'s', '<p style=\"padding: 0px; margin: 1.333em 0px; line-height: 1.333; width: 415px; height: auto; font-family: arial, sans-serif; font-size: 12px; \">Alpha Plus Group Limited acquired St Anthony&rsquo;s School as part of its growth and development strategy.</p>\n\n<p style=\"padding: 0px; margin: 1.333em 0px; line-height: 1.333; width: 415px; height: auto; font-family: arial, sans-serif; font-size: 12px; \">St Anthony&rsquo;s School is a highly successful Roman Catholic preparatory school for boys between the ages of 5 and 13. The acquisition has received support from the Diocese of Westminster with Alpha Plus fully committed to ensuring the maintenance of the strong Catholic ethos of the school.</p>\n\n<p style=\"padding: 0px; margin: 1.333em 0px; line-height: 1.333; width: 415px; height: auto; font-family: arial, sans-serif; font-size: 12px; \">The Baker Tilly team, led by Jim Clifford, provided transaction support throughout the acquisition process, including negotiation support and deal structuring advice.</p>\n\n<p style=\"padding: 0px; margin: 1.333em 0px; line-height: 1.333; width: 415px; height: auto; font-family: arial, sans-serif; font-size: 12px; \"><em>&ldquo;In addition to the excellent quality of Jim&rsquo;s team and his exceptional ability as a negotiator, he brought a sensitivity and understanding of St Anthony&rsquo;s position as a Catholic school which was both supportive and highly significant in securing the school&rsquo;s future. His work enabled the school to find a solution which meets the need of pupils, parents, staff and trustees and has provided a foundation for future development of the school&rsquo;s ethos and affiliation.&rdquo;</em><br />\n<strong>Phil Anderson, Chair of Board of Directors, St Anthony&rsquo;s School, Hampstead</strong></p>\n', '<p style=\"padding: 0px; margin: 1.333em 0px; line-height: 1.333; width: 415px; height: auto; font-family: arial, sans-serif; font-size: 12px; \">Alpha Plus G