sult.&rdquo;</em><br />\n<strong>Terry Furuzawa, Majority Shareholder, OCS London Ltd</strong></p>\n', '<p><span style=\"font-family: arial, sans-serif; font-size: 12px; line-height: 15px; \">Baker Tilly&rsquo;s M&amp;A and Private Equity team has successfully advised the shareholders on the sale of OCS London Ltd to its management team. The buy-out was supported by Centric Commercial Finance.</span></p>\n', '<p><span style=\"font-family: arial, sans-serif; font-size: 12px; line-height: 15px; \">Baker Tilly&rsquo;s M&amp;A and Private Equity team has successfully advised the shareholders on the sale of OCS London Ltd to its management team. The buy-out was supported by Centric Commercial Finance.</span></p>\n', 18, 0, 1, '2013-03-13 04:25:40', 0, '', 0),
(18, 'Nimans Holdings Ltd', 'Nimans Holdings Ltd', '<p style=\"padding: 0px; margin: 1.333em 0px; line-height: 1.333; width: 415px; height: auto; font-family: arial, sans-serif; font-size: 12px; \">Baker Tilly&#39;s&nbsp; Manchester Corporate Finance team has recently advised telecoms distributor, Nimans&nbsp;Holdings Limited, on its &pound;12.45m acquisition of Rocom Limited from its AIM listed parent AT Communications Group.</p>\n\n<p style=\"padding: 0px; margin: 1.333em 0px; line-height: 1.333; width: 415px; height: auto; font-family: arial, sans-serif; font-size: 12px; \">Both companies distribute equipment including headsets,PA and audio conferencing systems to resellers, corporates and retail customers. The deal has created a group with a combined turnover&nbsp;<br />\nof almost &pound;100 million and a workforce of more than 400 people.</p>\n\n<p style=\"padding: 0px; margin: 1.333em 0px; line-height: 1.333; width: 415px; height: auto; font-family: arial, sans-serif; font-size: 12px; \">Baker Tilly&nbsp; acted as lead adviser to Nimans on the acquisiton,obtaining&nbsp;debt funding, negotiating the deal with vendor and project managing the transaction through to completion.<br />\n<br />\n<em>&quot;The deal certainly strengthens the position of both companies in what is a highly competitive&nbsp;sector. This transaction points to continued consolidation within the telecoms sector-&nbsp; as well as&nbsp; highlighting that,despite challenging environment for raising finance, significant deals can still&nbsp; be done.&quot;</em><br />\n<strong>Adrian&nbsp; Gare Corporate Finance Director, Baker&nbsp; Tilly</strong></p>\n', '<p style=\"padding: 0px; margin: 1.333em 0px; line-height: 1.333; width: 415px; height: auto; font-family: arial, sans-serif; font-size: 12px; \">Baker Tilly&#39;s&nbsp; Manchester Corporate Finance team has recently advised telecoms distributor, Nimans&nbsp;Holdings Limited, on its &pound;12.45m acquisition of Rocom Limited from its AIM listed parent AT Communications Group.</p>\n\n<p style=\"padding: 0px; margin: 1.333em 0px; line-height: 1.333; width: 415px; height: auto; font-family: arial, sans-serif; font-size: 12px; \">Both companies distribute equipment including headsets,PA and audio conferencing systems to resellers, corporates and retail customers. The deal has created a group with a combined turnover&nbsp;<br />\nof almost &pound;100 million and a workforce of more than 400 people.</p>\n\n<p style=\"padding: 0px; margin: 1.333em 0px; line-height: 1.333; width: 415px; height: auto; font-family: arial, sans-serif; font-size: 12px; \">Baker Tilly&nbsp; acted as lead adviser to Nimans on the acquisiton,obtaining&nbsp;debt funding, negotiating the deal with vendor and project managing the transaction through to completion.<br />\n<br />\n<em>&quot;The deal certainly strengthens the position of both companies in what is a highly competitive&nbsp;sector. This transaction points to continued consolidation within the telecoms sector-&nbsp; as well as&nbsp; highlighting that,despite challenging environment for raising finance, significant deals can still&nbsp; be done.&quot;</em><br />\n<strong>Adrian&nbsp; Gare Corporate Finance Director, Baker&nbsp; Tilly</strong></p>\n', '<p><span style=\"font-family: arial, sans-serif; font-size: 12px; line-height: 15px; \">Baker Tilly&#39;s Manchester Corporate Finance team has recently advised telecoms distributor, Nimans Holdings Limited, on its &pound;12.45m acquisition of Rocom Limited from its AIM listed parent AT Communications Group.</span></p>\n', '<p><span style=\"font-family: arial, sans-serif; font-size: 12px; line-height: 15px; \">Baker Tilly&#39;s Manchester Corporate Finance team has recently advised telecoms distributor, Nimans Holdings Limited, on its &pound;12.45m acquisition of Rocom Limited from its AIM listed parent AT Communications Group.</span></p>\n', 18, 0, 1, '2013-03-13 04:27:39', 0, '', 0),
(19, 'Limehouse Software', 'Limehouse Software', '<p style=\"padding: 0px; margin: 1.333em 0px; line-height: 1.333; width: 415px; height: auto; font-family: arial, sans-serif; font-size: 12px; \">Limehouse Group... linked!</p>\n\n<p style=\"padding: 0px; margin: 1.333em 0px; line-height: 1.333; width: 415px; height: auto; font-family: arial, sans-serif; font-size: 12px; \">Baker Tilly&#39;s M&amp;A and Private Equity team have recently advised on the sale of The Limehouse Group, an award winning stakeholder communications business. Limehouse was sold to Trident, a corporate communications specialist and was backed by newly formed private equity house, Iceni Capital.</p>\n\n<p style=\"padding: 0px; margin: 1.333em 0px; line-height: 1.333; width: 415px; height: auto; font-family: arial, sans-serif; font-size: 12px; \">Robert Donaldson and Ali Aneizi of Baker Tilly led and managed an auction. This was a complicated deal given that Iceni Capital were backing the management teams of both Trident and Limehouse in a simultaneous and double buy out. Both transactions were run in parallel and involved five legal firms, three sets of principals, two groups of investing management teams, two separate financial and legal due diligence processes and a mix of exiting and investing shareholders.</p>\n\n<p style=\"padding: 0px; margin: 1.333em 0px; line-height: 1.333; width: 415px; height: auto; font-family: arial, sans-serif; font-size: 12px; \">Completion of the double buy out has led to the creation of an enlarged private equity backed marketing services platform offering corporate, public and not for profit clients a wide range of end to end design and communications solutions.</p>\n\n<p style=\"padding: 0px; margin: 1.333em 0px; line-height: 1.333; width: 415px; height: auto; font-family: arial, sans-serif; font-size: 12px; \"><em>&lsquo;&lsquo;At all times the team at Baker Tilly provided excellent advice and a cool and confident approach. Having never been through a transaction like this before it was reassuring to have experienced people in our corner. Without their help I truly believe this deal wouldn&rsquo;t have gone through.&rdquo;</em><br />\n<strong>Giles Welch, Managing Director, The Limehouse Group</strong></p>\n', '<p style=\"padding: 0px; margin: 1.333em 0px; line-height: 1.333; width: 415px; height: auto; font-family: arial, sans-serif; font-size: 12px; \">Limehouse Group... linked!</p>\n\n<p style=\"padding: 0px; margin: 1.333em 0px; line-height: 1.333; width: 415px; height: auto; font-family: arial, sans-serif; font-size: 12px; \">Baker Tilly&#39;s M&amp;A and Private Equity team have recently advised on the sale of The Limehouse Group, an award winning stakeholder communications business. Limehouse was sold to Trident, a corporate communications specialist and was backed by newly formed private equity house, Iceni Capital.</p>\n\n<p style=\"padding: 0px; margin: 1.333em 0px; line-height: 1.333; width: 415px; height: auto; font-family: arial, sans-serif; font-size: 12px; \">Robert Donaldson and Ali Aneizi of Baker Tilly led and managed an auction. This was a complicated deal given that Iceni Capital were backing the management teams of both Trident and Limehouse in a simultaneous and double buy out. Both transactions were run in parallel and involved five legal firms, three sets of principals, two groups of investing management teams, two separate financial and legal due diligence processes and a mix of exiting and investing shareholders.</p>\n\n<p style=\"padding: 0px; margin: 1.333em 0px; line-height: 1.333; width: 415px; height: auto; font-family: arial, sans-serif; font-size: 12px; \">Completion of the double buy out has led to the creation of an enlarged private equity backed marketing services platform offering corporate, public and not for profit clients a wide range of end to end design and communications solutions.</p>\n\n<p style=\"padding: 0px; margin: 1.333em 0px; line-height: 1.333; width: 415px; height: auto; font-family: arial, sans-serif; font-size: 12px; \"><em>&lsquo;&lsquo;At all times the team at Baker Tilly provided excellent advice and a cool and confident approach. Having never been through a transaction like this before it was reassuring to have experienced people in our corner. Without their help I truly believe this deal wouldn&rsquo;t have gone through.&rdquo;</em><br />\n<strong>Giles Welch, Managing Director, The Limehouse Group</strong></p>\n', '<p><span style=\"font-family: arial, sans-serif; font-size: 12px; line-height: 15px; \">Baker Tilly&#39;s M&amp;A and Private Equity team have recently advised on the sale of The Limehouse Group, an award winning stakeholder communications business.</span></p>\n', '<p><span style=\"font-family: arial, sans-serif; font-size: 12px; line-height: 15px; \">Baker Tilly&#39;s M&amp;A and Private Equity team have recently advised on the sale of The Limehouse Group, an award winning stakeholder communications business.</span></p>\n', 18, 0, 1, '2013-03-13 04:28:34', 0, '', 0),
(20, 'Kornicis Group Ltd', 'Kornicis Group Ltd', '<p><span style=\"font-family: arial, sans-serif; font-size: 12px; line-height: normal; \">Kornicis Group Limited, led by former TigerTiger chief Nick Tamblyn, and backed by NBGI Private Equity, has acquired 17 sites and a range of brands including the Jamies and Henry J Bean Brands out of the administration of The Food &amp; Drink Group Plc. In addition to the 17 sites which have geographic focus on London, came 17 franchise sites under the Henry J Beans brand - including two within Hilton Hotels and 15 international sites.</span><br style=\"font-family: arial, sans-serif; font-size: 12px; line-height: normal; \" />\n<span style=\"font-family: arial, sans-serif; font-size: 12px; line-height: normal; \">&nbsp;</span><br style=\"font-family: arial, sans-serif; font-size: 12px; line-height: normal; \" />\n<span style=\"font-family: arial, sans-serif; font-size: 12px; line-height: normal; \">Baker Tilly provided due diligence on the acquired sites, structuring advice and negotiation support to NBGI to enable the transaction to complete within a tight deadline.</span><br style=\"font-family: arial, sans-serif; font-size: 12px; line-height: normal; \" />\n<span style=\"font-family: arial, sans-serif; font-size: 12px; line-height: normal; \">&nbsp;</span><br style=\"font-family: arial, sans-serif; font-size: 12px; line-height: normal; \" />\n<span style=\"font-family: arial, sans-serif; font-size: 12px; line-height: normal; \">&quot;With a wealth of experience in the sector, and first-hand experience of buy-side and sell-side in Administrations, Jim and the team were an obvious choice for this transaction&quot;</span><br style=\"font-family: arial, sans-serif; font-size: 12px; line-height: normal; \" />\n<span style=\"font-family: arial, sans-serif; font-size: 12px; line-height: normal; \">Mark Owen, NBGI Private Equity</span><br style=\"font-family: arial, sans-serif; font-size: 12px; line-height: normal; \" />\n<span styl