ns-serif; font-size: 12px; line-height: normal; \">&quot;With a wealth of experience in the sector, and first-hand experience of buy-side and sell-side in Administrations, Jim and the team were an obvious choice for this transaction&quot;</span><br style=\"font-family: arial, sans-serif; font-size: 12px; line-height: normal; \" />\n<span style=\"font-family: arial, sans-serif; font-size: 12px; line-height: normal; \">Mark Owen, NBGI Private Equity</span><br style=\"font-family: arial, sans-serif; font-size: 12px; line-height: normal; \" />\n<span style=\"font-family: arial, sans-serif; font-size: 12px; line-height: normal; \">&nbsp;</span><br style=\"font-family: arial, sans-serif; font-size: 12px; line-height: normal; \" />\n<em style=\"font-family: arial, sans-serif; font-size: 12px; line-height: normal; \">&quot;Without the Baker Tilly input, this deal might never have happened. They were there with the right input at just the right time. This gives us a great foundation for the future.&quot;</em><br />\n<strong style=\"font-family: arial, sans-serif; font-size: 12px; line-height: normal; \">Nick Tamblyn, CEO, Kornicis Group</strong></p>\n', '<p><span style=\"font-family: arial, sans-serif; font-size: 12px; line-height: 15px; \">Kornicis Group Limited, led by former TigerTiger chief Nick Tamblyn, and backed by NBGI Private Equity, has acquired 17 sites and a range of brands including the Jamies and Henry J Bean Brands out of the administration of The Food &amp; Drink Group Plc.</span></p>\n', '<p><span style=\"font-family: arial, sans-serif; font-size: 12px; line-height: 15px; \">Kornicis Group Limited, led by former TigerTiger chief Nick Tamblyn, and backed by NBGI Private Equity, has acquired 17 sites and a range of brands including the Jamies and Henry J Bean Brands out of the administration of The Food &amp; Drink Group Plc.</span></p>\n', 18, 0, 1, '2013-03-13 04:29:22', 0, '', 0),
(21, 'Highland Spring Ltd', 'Highland Spring Ltd', '<p style=\"padding: 0px; margin: 1.333em 0px; line-height: 1.333; width: 415px; height: auto; font-family: arial, sans-serif; font-size: 12px; \">Highland Spring, a leading supplier of branded bottled water in the UK,has successfully acquired the own-lab bottled water business of Greencore pic for up to &pound;17.5 million.</p>\n\n<p style=\"padding: 0px; margin: 1.333em 0px; line-height: 1.333; width: 415px; height: auto; font-family: arial, sans-serif; font-size: 12px; \">The acquisition will establish Highland Spring as the UK&#39;s largest bottled water supplier, enhancing their prod offering to the UK grocers and food industry. With an estimated combined sales volume in excess of 350 millio litres a year, Highland Spring has the ability to double its existing sales volume, taking the company a step clo to achieving its aspiration of becoming a &pound;100 million&nbsp; turnover business.</p>\n\n<p style=\"padding: 0px; margin: 1.333em 0px; line-height: 1.333; width: 415px; height: auto; font-family: arial, sans-serif; font-size: 12px; \">Baker Tilly&#39;s&nbsp; Transaction Services team undertook acquisition due diligence for Highland Spring,&nbsp;<br />\nensuring that cost structure and run-rate profitability&nbsp; of the Greencore water operations was&nbsp;<br />\nclearly understood. This enable management to confidently project the benefits from combining the two businesses.</p>\n\n<p style=\"padding: 0px; margin: 1.333em 0px; line-height: 1.333; width: 415px; height: auto; font-family: arial, sans-serif; font-size: 12px; \"><em>&quot;This&nbsp; was our first&nbsp; experience of working with Baker Tilly and a most successful opener! They were able to quickly summarise the key issues and focus our attention on the most relevant points. They were thoroughly professio and friendly-&nbsp; the latter being very important in the Highland Spring culture.&quot;</em><br />\n<strong>Murray Falconer,Finance Director, Highland Spring Limited</strong></p>\n', '<p style=\"padding: 0px; margin: 1.333em 0px; line-height: 1.333; width: 415px; height: auto; font-family: arial, sans-serif; font-size: 12px; \">Highland Spring, a leading supplier of branded bottled water in the UK,has successfully acquired the own-lab bottled water business of Greencore pic for up to &pound;17.5 million.</p>\n\n<p style=\"padding: 0px; margin: 1.333em 0px; line-height: 1.333; width: 415px; height: auto; font-family: arial, sans-serif; font-size: 12px; \">The acquisition will establish Highland Spring as the UK&#39;s largest bottled water supplier, enhancing their prod offering to the UK grocers and food industry. With an estimated combined sales volume in excess of 350 millio litres a year, Highland Spring has the ability to double its existing sales volume, taking the company a step clo to achieving its aspiration of becoming a &pound;100 million&nbsp; turnover business.</p>\n\n<p style=\"padding: 0px; margin: 1.333em 0px; line-height: 1.333; width: 415px; height: auto; font-family: arial, sans-serif; font-size: 12px; \">Baker Tilly&#39;s&nbsp; Transaction Services team undertook acquisition due diligence for Highland Spring,&nbsp;<br />\nensuring that cost structure and run-rate profitability&nbsp; of the Greencore water operations was&nbsp;<br />\nclearly understood. This enable management to confidently project the benefits from combining the two businesses.</p>\n\n<p style=\"padding: 0px; margin: 1.333em 0px; line-height: 1.333; width: 415px; height: auto; font-family: arial, sans-serif; font-size: 12px; \"><em>&quot;This&nbsp; was our first&nbsp; experience of working with Baker Tilly and a most successful opener! They were able to quickly summarise the key issues and focus our attention on the most relevant points. They were thoroughly professio and friendly-&nbsp; the latter being very important in the Highland Spring culture.&quot;</em><br />\n<strong>Murray Falconer,Finance Director, Highland Spring Limited</strong></p>\n', '<p><span style=\"font-family: arial, sans-serif; font-size: 12px; line-height: 15px; \">Highland Spring, a leading supplier of branded bottled water in the UK,has successfully acquired the own-lab bottled water business of Greencore pic for up to &pound;17.5 million.</span></p>\n', '<p><span style=\"font-family: arial, sans-serif; font-size: 12px; line-height: 15px; \">Highland Spring, a leading supplier of branded bottled water in the UK,has successfully acquired the own-lab bottled water business of Greencore pic for up to &pound;17.5 million.</span></p>\n', 30, 0, 1, '2013-03-13 04:30:53', 0, '', 0);
