(22, 'Garner PLC', 'Garner PLC', '<p style=\"padding: 0px; margin: 1.333em 0px; line-height: 1.333; width: 415px; height: auto; font-family: arial, sans-serif; font-size: 12px; \">Baker Tilly is please to announce the completion of the &pound;5.5m reverse acquisition of the Norman Broadbent executive search business and readmission to AIM by Garner PLC.</p>\n\n<p style=\"padding: 0px; margin: 1.333em 0px; line-height: 1.333; width: 415px; height: auto; font-family: arial, sans-serif; font-size: 12px; \">The acquisition makes Garner PLC group one of the largest providers of board level search services in the UK, with a team of more that 65 people between the two brands. The group already provides generalist executive search, including CEOs and HR directors, with a dedicated HR practice, through its boutique provider, Garner International.</p>\n\n<p style=\"padding: 0px; margin: 1.333em 0px; line-height: 1.333; width: 415px; height: auto; font-family: arial, sans-serif; font-size: 12px; \">Baker Tilly acted as reporting accountants providing the working capital comfort on the new enlarged group and the historical financial due diligence on the three limited companies that made up the target business.</p>\n\n<p style=\"padding: 0px; margin: 1.333em 0px; line-height: 1.333; width: 415px; height: auto; font-family: arial, sans-serif; font-size: 12px; \"><em>&ldquo;Baker Tilly were an important part of the deal team in what is a transformational acquisition for Garner Plc. Their diligent and proactive approach added value to the transaction process and helped resolve issues rather than creating barriers.&rdquo;</em><br />\n<strong>Sue O Brien, Managing Director, Garner PLC</strong></p>\n', '<p style=\"padding: 0px; margin: 1.333em 0px; line-height: 1.333; width: 415px; height: auto; font-family: arial, sans-serif; font-size: 12px; \">Baker Tilly is please to announce the completion of the &pound;5.5m reverse acquisition of the Norman Broadbent executive search business and readmission to AIM by Garner PLC.</p>\n\n<p style=\"padding: 0px; margin: 1.333em 0px; line-height: 1.333; width: 415px; height: auto; font-family: arial, sans-serif; font-size: 12px; \">The acquisition makes Garner PLC group one of the largest providers of board level search services in the UK, with a team of more that 65 people between the two brands. The group already provides generalist executive search, including CEOs and HR directors, with a dedicated HR practice, through its boutique provider, Garner International.</p>\n\n<p style=\"padding: 0px; margin: 1.333em 0px; line-height: 1.333; width: 415px; height: auto; font-family: arial, sans-serif; font-size: 12px; \">Baker Tilly acted as reporting accountants providing the working capital comfort on the new enlarged group and the historical financial due diligence on the three limited companies that made up the target business.</p>\n\n<p style=\"padding: 0px; margin: 1.333em 0px; line-height: 1.333; width: 415px; height: auto; font-family: arial, sans-serif; font-size: 12px; \"><em>&ldquo;Baker Tilly were an important part of the deal team in what is a transformational acquisition for Garner Plc. Their diligent and proactive approach added value to the transaction process and helped resolve issues rather than creating barriers.&rdquo;</em><br />\n<strong>Sue O Brien, Managing Director, Garner PLC</strong></p>\n', '<p><span style=\"font-family: arial, sans-serif; font-size: 12px; line-height: 15px; \">Baker Tilly is please to announce the completion of the &pound;5.5m reverse acquisition of the Norman Broadbent executive search business and readmission to AIM by Garner PLC.</span></p>\n', '<p><span style=\"font-family: arial, sans-serif; font-size: 12px; line-height: 15px; \">Baker Tilly is please to announce the completion of the &pound;5.5m reverse acquisition of the Norman Broadbent executive search business and readmission to AIM by Garner PLC.</span></p>\n', 30, 0, 1, '2013-03-13 04:32:00', 0, '', 0),
(23, 'Excel Leisure Products Ltd', 'Excel Leisure Products Ltd', '<p style=\"padding: 0px; margin: 1.333em 0px; line-height: 1.333; width: 415px; height: auto; font-family: arial, sans-serif; font-size: 12px; \">Baker Tilly&rsquo;s Leeds corporate finance team recently advised the majority shareholders of Excel Leisure Products Limited on the sale of their business to their key competitor, Simply Pool Limited. Excel Leisure Products manufacture and distribute top quality pool and football tables for both commercial and domestic use.</p>\n\n<p style=\"padding: 0px; margin: 1.333em 0px; line-height: 1.333; width: 415px; height: auto; font-family: arial, sans-serif; font-size: 12px; \">The transaction brought together the two premium brands in the sector and provides a platform for the combined entity to become the stand alone market leader in the sector.</p>\n\n<p style=\"padding: 0px; margin: 1.333em 0px; line-height: 1.333; width: 415px; height: auto; font-family: arial, sans-serif; font-size: 12px; \"><em>&ldquo;The pro-active advice provided by Baker Tilly during the sale process was invaluable. Given the sensitive nature of exploring a sale to a major competitor, significant care was required in terms of the provision of information and negotiations, which Baker Tilly handled very well.&rdquo;</em><br />\n<strong>Stan McKenna, Managing Director, Excel Leisure Products Limited</strong></p>\n', '<p style=\"padding: 0px; margin: 1.333em 0px; line-height: 1.333; width: 415px; height: auto; font-family: arial, sans-serif; font-size: 12px; \">Baker Tilly&rsquo;s Leeds corporate finance team recently advised the majority shareholders of Excel Leisure Products Limited on the sale of their business to their key competitor, Simply Pool Limited. Excel Leisure Products manufacture and distribute top quality pool and football tables for both commercial and domestic use.</p>\n\n<p style=\"padding: 0px; margin: 1.333em 0px; line-height: 1.333; width: 415px; height: auto; font-family: arial, sans-serif; font-size: 12px; \">The transaction brought together the two premium brands in the sector and provides a platform for the combined entity to become the stand alone market leader in the sector.</p>\n\n<p style=\"padding: 0px; margin: 1.333em 0px; line-height: 1.333; width: 415px; height: auto; font-family: arial, sans-serif; font-size: 12px; \"><em>&ldquo;The pro-active advice provided by Baker Tilly during the sale process was invaluable. Given the sensitive nature of exploring a sale to a major competitor, significant care was required in terms of the provision of information and negotiations, which Baker Tilly handled very well.&rdquo;</em><br />\n<strong>Stan McKenna, Managing Director, Excel Leisure Products Limited</strong></p>\n', '<p><span style=\"font-family: arial, sans-serif; font-size: 12px; line-height: 15px; \">Baker Tilly&rsquo;s Leeds corporate finance team recently advised the majority shareholders of Excel Leisure Products Limited on the sale of their business to their key competitor, Simply Pool Limited.</span></p>\n', '<p><span style=\"font-family: arial, sans-serif; font-size: 12px; line-height: 15px; \">Baker Tilly&rsquo;s Leeds corporate finance team recently advised the majority shareholders of Excel Leisure Products Limited on the sale of their business to their key competitor, Simply Pool Limited.</span></p>\n', 30, 0, 1, '2013-03-13 04:33:20', 0, '', 0),
(24, 'BSW Timber Ltd', 'BSW Timber Ltd', '<p style=\"padding: 0px; margin: 1.333em 0px; line-height: 1.333; width: 415px; height: auto; font-family: arial, sans-serif; font-size: 12px; \">BSW Timber is already the largest sawmilling group in the UK and this deal will increase its sawn&nbsp;timber capa to more than one million&nbsp; m3 per annum.&nbsp; The 56 hectare Howie Forest Products sawmill&nbsp;in Dalbeattie has a turnover of &pound;30m and will remain a distinct&nbsp; entity within&nbsp; the BSW Group.</p>\n\n<p style=\"padding: 0px; margin: 1.333em 0px; line-height: 1.333; width: 415px; height: auto; font-family: arial, sans-serif; font-size: 12px; \">The merger of these premier Scottish sawmilling companies forms part of the long-term expansion drive aime enhancing the future profitability&nbsp; of the group and security to its customers and&nbsp; suppliers.<br />\n<br />\n<em>&ldquo;Through their understanding of the key business drivers in the sector and their responsiveness and delivery the Baker Tilly team played a key role in the successful completion of what is a landmark acquisition for BSW.&rdquo;</em>&nbsp;<br />\nHoward Jones, Finance Director, BSW Timber</p>\n', '<p style=\"padding: 0px; margin: 1.333em 0px; line-height: 1.333; width: 415px; height: auto; font-family: arial, sans-serif; font-size: 12px; \">BSW Timber is already the largest sawmilling group in the UK and this deal will increase its sawn&nbsp;timber capa to more than one million&nbsp; m3 per annum.&nbsp; The 56 hectare Howie Forest Products sawmill&nbsp;in Dalbeattie has a turnover of &pound;30m and will remain a distinct&nbsp; entity within&nbsp; the BSW Group.</p>\n\n<p style=\"padding: 0px; margin: 1.333em 0px; line-height: 1.333; width: 415px; height: auto; font-family: arial, sans-serif; font-size: 12px; \">The merger of these premier Scottish sawmilling companies forms part of the long-term expansion drive aime enhancing the future profitability&nbsp; of the group and security to its customers and&nbsp; suppliers.<br />\n<br />\n<em>&ldquo;Through their understanding of the key business drivers in the sector and their responsiveness and delivery the Baker Tilly team played a key role in the successful completion of what is a landmark acquisition for BSW.&rdquo;</em>&nbsp;<br />\nHoward Jones, Finance Director, BSW Timber</p>\n', '<p><span style=\"font-family: arial, sans-serif; font-size: 12px; line-height: 15px; \">BSW Timber is already the largest sawmilling group in the UK and this deal will increase its sawn timber capa to more than one million m3 per annum.</span></p>\n', '<p><span style=\"font-family: arial, sans-serif; font-size: 12px; line-height: 15px; \">BSW Timber is already the largest sawmilling group in the UK and this deal will increase its sawn timber capa to more than one million m3 per annum.</span></p>\n', 30, 0, 1, '2013-03-13 04:33:59', 0, '', 0),
