(33, '4D Interactive Ltd', '4D Interactive Ltd', '<p class=\"intro\" style=\"padding: 0px; margin: 15px 0px; line-height: 1.143; font-size: 1.16667em; width: 415px; height: auto; font-family: arial, sans-serif; \">The executive directors of Intermediactive Holdings Ltd have successfully acquired the business from Promethean Investments Fund LP for an enterprise value of c.&pound;21m. The group&#39;s principal trading entity 4D Interactive Ltd (&#39;4D&#39;) provides multi-platform telecommunications services to both consumers and businesses. Founded in 1993, 4D is a market leader in the provision of interactive entertainment services through voice, TV and web platforms.</p>\n\n<p style=\"padding: 0px; margin: 1.333em 0px; line-height: 1.333; width: 415px; height: auto; font-family: arial, sans-serif; font-size: 12px; \">The deal was financed with senior debt from Barclays Bank plc as well as management&rsquo;s re-investment of their previous minority interest and a vendor loan note.&nbsp; Baker Tilly&#39;s Transaction Services team performed financial due diligence for Barclays Bank plc in support of their &pound;12.5m lend.</p>\n\n<p style=\"padding: 0px; margin: 1.333em 0px; line-height: 1.333; width: 415px; height: auto; font-family: arial, sans-serif; font-size: 12px; \"><em>&ldquo;We are excited to be able to take control of the group at a time where the business is in growth and there are many opportunities to develop new services and extend our reach to consumers particularly across new digital media. Both Baker Tilly and Barclays have again shown their focus and devotion to the middle market at a time when many others are ignoring this lucrative &lsquo;engine room&rsquo; of growth.&rdquo;</em><br />\nDavid Lee, Managing Director, Intermediactive Holdings Ltd</p>\n', '<p class=\"intro\" style=\"padding: 0px; margin: 15px 0px; line-height: 1.143; font-size: 1.16667em; width: 415px; height: auto; font-family: arial, sans-serif; \">The executive directors of Int