 acquired the business from Promethean Investments Fund LP for an enterprise value of c.&pound;21m.</span></p>\n', 18, 86, 1, '2013-03-13 04:44:55', 0, '', 0),
(34, 'Kelway Holdings Ltd', 'Kelway Holdings Ltd', '<p class=\"intro\" style=\"padding: 0px; margin: 15px 0px; line-height: 1.143; font-size: 1.16667em; width: 415px; height: auto; font-family: arial, sans-serif; \">Kelway, the UK&rsquo;s leading mid-market IT reseller, has acquired Panacea Services Ltd. The seal is Kelway&rsquo;s third acquisition since Core Capital invested in the business in 2006 and creates a combined business with revenues in excess of &pound;140 million.</p>\n\n<p style=\"padding: 0px; margin: 1.333em 0px; line-height: 1.333; width: 415px; height: auto; font-family: arial, sans-serif; font-size: 12px; \">The acquisition of Panacea will further strengthen Kelway&rsquo;s position as one of the fastest growing IT resellers, and will enhance their established strengths in product consultancy and lifecycle solutions.</p>\n\n<p style=\"padding: 0px; margin: 1.333em 0px; line-height: 1.333; width: 415px; height: auto; font-family: arial, sans-serif; font-size: 12px; \">Baker Tilly&rsquo;s Corporate Finance team advised on the deal structure and undertook the acquisition due diligence process including looking at some of the ongoing tax structures for the combined group.</p>\n\n<p style=\"padding: 0px; margin: 1.333em 0px; line-height: 1.333; width: 415px; height: auto; font-family: arial, sans-serif; font-size: 12px; \"><em>&ldquo;We utilise Baker Tilly for Audit, Tax and Corporate Finance. Their in-depth knowledge of our business proved invaluable in enabling us to complete a very complicated transaction.&rdquo;</em><br />\nCraig Compton, Financial Director, Kelway (UK) Ltd</p>\n', '<p class=\"intro\" style=\"padding: 0px; margin: 15px 0px; line-height: 1.143; font-size: 1.16667em; width: 415px; height: auto; font-family: arial, sans-serif; \">Kelway, the UK&rsquo;s leading mid-market IT reseller, has acquired Panacea Services Ltd. The seal is Kelway&rsquo;s third acquisition since Core Capital invested in the business in 2006 and creates a combined business with revenues in excess of &pound;140 million.</p>\n\n<p style=\"padding: 0px; margin: 1.333em 0px; line-height: 1.333; width: 415px; height: auto; font-family: arial, sans-serif; font-size: 12px; \">The acquisition of Panacea will further strengthen Kelway&rsquo;s position as one of the fastest growing IT resellers, and will enhance their established strengths in product consultancy and lifecycle solutions.</p>\n\n<p style=\"padding: 0px; margin: 1.333em 0px; line-height: 1.333; width: 415px; height: auto; font-family: arial, sans-serif; font-size: 12px; \">Baker Tilly&rsquo;s Corporate Finance team advised on the deal structure and undertook the acquisition due diligence process including looking at some of the ongoing tax structures for the combined group.</p>\n\n<p style=\"padding: 0px; margin: 1.333em 0px; line-height: 1.333; width: 415px; height: auto; font-family: arial, sans-serif; font-size: 12px; \"><em>&ldquo;We utilise Baker Tilly for Audit, Tax and Corporate Finance. Their in-depth knowledge of our business proved invaluable in enabling us to complete a very complicated transaction.&rdquo;</em><br />\nCraig Compton, Financial Director, Kelway (UK) Ltd</p>\n', '<p><span style=\"font-family: arial, sans-serif; font-size: 12px; line-height: 15px; \">Kelway, the UK&rsquo;s leading mid-market IT reseller, has acquired Panacea Services Ltd.</span></p>\n', '<p><span style=\"font-family: arial, sans-serif; font-size: 12px; line-height: 15px; \">Kelway, the UK&rsquo;s leading mid-market IT reseller, has acquired Panacea Services Ltd.</span></p>\n', 18, 86, 1, '2013-03-13 04:45:36', 0, '', 0),
(35, 'Shed Productions', 'Shed Productions', '<p class=\"intro\" style=\"padding: 0px; margin: 15px 0px; line-height: 1.143; font-size: 1.16667em; width: 415px; height: auto; font-family: arial, sans-serif; \">In March 2005, the Capital Markets team at Baker Tilly completed work on the IPO of Shed Productions plc, one of the UK&rsquo;s largest independent production companies.</p>\n\n<p style=\"padding: 0px; margin: 1.333em 0px; line-height: 1.333; width: 415px; height: auto; font-family: arial, sans-serif; font-size: 12px; \">Shed is set to grow its existing core productions of Bad Girls and Footballers&rsquo; Wives to five contemporary and original dramas in the next year.</p>\n\n<p style=\"padding: 0px; margin: 1.333em 0px; line-height: 1.333; width: 415px; height: auto; font-family: arial, sans-serif; font-size: 12px; \">Baker Tilly, as reporting accountants, provided advice and guidance to Shed&rsquo;s gifted home-grown team in a transaction that was significantly oversubscribed.</p>\n\n<p style=\"padding: 0px; margin: 1.333em 0px; line-height: 1.333; width: 415px; height: auto; font-family: arial, sans-serif; font-size: 12px; \"><em>&ldquo;Baker Tilly delivered high quality, timely reports, providing a valuable contribution to the success of the IPO process. We are pleased to have them as our advisers.&rdquo;</em><br />\nEileen Gallagher, Chief Executive, Shed Productions plc</p>\n', '<p class=\"intro\" style=\"padding: 0px; margin: 15px 0px; line-height: 1.143; font-size: 1.16667em; width: 415px; height: auto; font-family: arial, sans-serif; \">In March 2005, the Capital Markets team at Baker Tilly completed work on the IPO of Shed Productions plc, one of the UK&rsquo;s largest independent production companies.</p>\n\n<p style=\"padding: 0px; margin: 1.333em 0px; line-height: 1.333; width: 415px; height: auto; font-family: arial, sans-serif; font-size: 12px; \">Shed is set to grow its existing core productions of Bad Girls and Footballers&rsquo; Wives to five