(36, 'DP Poland Plc', 'DP Poland Plc', '<p class=\"intro\" style=\"padding: 0px; margin: 15px 0px; line-height: 1.143; font-size: 1.16667em; width: 415px; height: auto; font-family: arial, sans-serif; \">Baker Tilly&#39;s Capital Markets team acted as reporting accountants on the successful IPO of DP Poland Pic to AIM.</p>\n\n<p style=\"padding: 0px; margin: 1.333em 0px; line-height: 1.333; width: 415px; height: auto; font-family: arial, sans-serif; font-size: 12px; \">DP Poland successfully secured the master franchise agreement for Domino&#39;s Pizza in Poland. Domino&#39;s Pizza is the world&#39;s leading pizza delivery brand with 9,000 outlets in 60 countries. The&nbsp;<br />\nmanagement team includes Richard Worthington and Peter Shaw who have a proven track record in the Polish market due to their involvem in coffeeheaven international in Poland which was sold to Costa Coffee for &pound;36 million&nbsp; in February 2010.</p>\n\n<p style=\"padding: 0px; margin: 1.333em 0px; line-height: 1.333; width: 415px; height: auto; font-family: arial, sans-serif; font-size: 12px; \">The placing raised &pound;6.5 million&nbsp; (before expenses) giving the company a market capitalisation of around &pound;9.9 million. Using the strength of the brand and their knowledge of the Polish market, DP Poland aims to roll out more than 50 stores in 4-5yrs.</p>\n\n<p style=\"padding: 0px; margin: 1.333em 0px; line-height: 1.333; width: 415px; height: auto; font-family: arial, sans-serif; font-size: 12px; \">In addition to the reporting accountant role,the Baker Tilly team also advised DP Poland in&nbsp;<br />\nrelation to the selection and establishment of employee incentive schemes.</p>\n\n<p style=\"padding: 0px; margin: 1.333em 0px; line-height: 1.333; width: 415px; height: auto; font-family: arial, sans-serif; font-size: 12px; \"><br />\n<em>&quot;The Baker Tilly Team worked efficiently with our finance team to ensure that the transaction timetable was adhered to and provided valuable input at this stage of our company&#39;s development.&quot;</em><br />\nRichard Worthington, Executive Chairman, DP Poland Pic</p>\n', '<p class=\"intro\" style=\"padding: 0px; margin: 15px 0px; line-height: 1.143; font-size: 1.16667em; width: 415px; height: auto; font-family: arial, sans-serif; \">Baker Tilly&#39;s Capital Markets team acted as reporting accountants on the successful IPO of DP Poland Pic to AIM.</p>\n\n<p style=\"padding: 0px; margin: 1.333em 0px; line-height: 1.333; width: 415px; height: auto; font-family: arial, sans-serif; font-size: 12px; \">DP Poland successfully secured the master franchise agreement for Domino&#39;s Pizza in Poland. Domino&#39;s Pizza is the world&#39;s leading pizza delivery brand with 9,000 outlets in 60 countries. The&nbsp;<br />\nmanagement team includes Richard Worthington and Peter Shaw who have a proven track record in the Polish market due to their involvem in coffeeheaven international in Poland which was sold to Costa Coffee for &pound;36 million&nbsp; in February 2010.</p>\n\n<p style=\"padding: 0px; margin: 1.333em 0px; line-height: 1.333; width: 415px; height: auto; font-family: arial, sans-serif; font-size: 12px; \">The placing raised &pound;6.5 million&nbsp; (before expenses) giving the company a market capitalisation of around &pound;9.9 million. Using the strength of the brand and their knowledge of the Polish market, DP Poland aims to roll out more than 50 stores in 4-5yrs.</p>\n\n<p style=\"padding: 0px; margin: 1.333em 0px; line-height: 1.333; width: 415px; height: auto; font-family: arial, sans-serif; font-size: 12px; \">In addition to the reporting accountant role,the Baker Tilly team also advised DP Poland in&nbsp;<br />\nrelation to the selection and establishment of employee incentive schemes.</p>\n\n<p style=\"padding: 0px; margin: 1.333em 0px; line-height: 1.333; width: 415px; height: auto; font-family: arial, sans-serif; font-size: 12px; \"><br />\n<em>&quot;The Baker Tilly Team worked efficiently with our finance team to ensure that the transaction timetable was adhered to and provided valuable input at this stage of our company&#39;s development.&quot;</em><br />\nRichard Worthington, Executive Chairman, DP Poland Pic</p>\n', '<p><span style=\"font-family: arial, sans-serif; font-size: 12px; line-height: 15px; \">Baker Tilly&#39;s Capital Markets team acted as reporting accountants on the successful IPO of DP Poland Pic to AIM.</span></p>\n', '<p><span style=\"font-family: arial, sans-serif; font-size: 12px; line-height: 15px; \">Baker Tilly&#39;s Capital Markets team acted as reporting accountants on the successful IPO of DP Poland Pic to AIM.</span></p>\n', 18, 83, 1, '2013-03-13 04:47:25', 0, '', 0),
(37, 'EMIS Group Plc', 'EMIS Group Plc', '<p class=\"intro\" style=\"padding: 0px; margin: 15px 0px; line-height: 1.143; font-size: 1.16667em; width: 415px; height: auto; font-family: arial, sans-serif; \">Baker Tilly&#39;s&nbsp;Capital Markets team acted as reporting accountants on the successful IPO&nbsp;of EMIS Group Plc to AIM.</p>\n\n<p style=\"padding: 0px; margin: 1.333em 0px; line-height: 1.333; width: 415px; height: auto; font-family: arial, sans-serif; font-size: 12px; \">EMIS is the leading provider of software to the healthcare industry, supplying over half of the GP practices across the UK. The company&#39;s innovative clinical software solutions are transforming patient care by providing secure access to patients&#39; records across the various levels of healthcare&nbsp;<br />\npractitioners.</p>\n\n<p style=\"padding: 0px; margin: 1.333em 0px; line-height: 1.333; width: 415px; height: auto; font-family: arial, sans-serif; font-size: 12px; \">The &pound;50 million&nbsp; placing, which was two times oversubscribed, valued the EMIS Group at &pound;175 million, making it one of the top 80 companies on AIM. On the first day of trading EMIS&#39; share price rose by 2 valuing the group at nearly &pound;200 million.</p>\n\n<p style=\"padding: 0px; margin: 1.333em 0px; line-height: 1.333; width: 415px; height: auto; font-family: arial, sans-serif; font-size: 12px; \"><br />\n<em>&quot;The Baker Tilly team, drawn from both the London and Leeds offices,provided a seamless service throughout. They were extremely professional and quickly got to grips with the different aspects of our business. Their&nbsp;responsiveness and effective liaison with our finance team and other advisors made a significant contribution&nbsp;to the smooth running of the transaction.&quot;</em><br />\nSean Riddell,Chief&nbsp; Executive Officer, EMIS Group Pic</p>\n', '<p class=\"intro\" style=\"padding: 0px; margin: 15px 0px; line-height: 1.143; font-size: 1.16667em; width: 415px; height: 