ional Insurance and related areas.</p>\n\n<p style=\"padding: 0px; margin: 1.333em 0px; line-height: 1.333; width: 415px; height: auto; font-family: arial, sans-serif; font-size: 12px;\"><strong>Employer consulting team</strong><br />\nAt Baker Tilly we have a specialist group dedicated to providing advice and services on employer consulting matters. Our solutions can help not only to reduce the overall payroll costs, but also provide real incentives for key staff.</p>\n\n<p style=\"padding: 0px; margin: 1.333em 0px; line-height: 1.333; width: 415px; height: auto; font-family: arial, sans-serif; font-size: 12px;\">We can work with you on all aspects of remuneration planning and tax risk management, including PAYE and NIC compliance. We&rsquo;ll help you avoid pitfalls in important areas such as:</p>\n\n<ul style=\"padding-right: 0px; padding-left: 0px; margin: 0.666em 0px; width: 415px; float: left; font-family: arial, sans-serif; font-size: 12px; line-height: normal;\">\n	<li style=\"padding: 0px 0px 0px 12px; margin: 0px; line-height: 1.333; background-image: url(http://www.bakertilly.co.uk/sitecollectionimages/presentation/bullet-black.gif); list-style-type: none; clear: both; float: left; width: 394.25px; background-position: 0px 0.5em; background-repeat: no-repeat no-repeat;\">reducing payroll costs</li>\n	<li style=\"padding: 0px 0px 0px 12px; margin: 0px; line-height: 1.333; background-image: url(http://www.bakertilly.co.uk/sitecollectionimages/presentation/bullet-black.gif); list-style-type: none; clear: both; float: left; width: 394.25px; background-position: 0px 0.5em; background-repeat: no-repeat no-repeat;\">share and share option schemes</li>\n	<li style=\"padding: 0px 0px 0px 12px; margin: 0px; line-height: 1.333; background-image: url(http://www.bakertilly.co.uk/sitecollectionimages/presentation/bullet-black.gif); list-style-type: none; clear: both; float: left; width: 394.25px; background-position: 0px 0.5em; background-repeat: no-repeat no-repeat;\">PAYE and NIC health checks</li>\n	<li style=\"padding: 0px 0px 0px 12px; margin: 0px; line-height: 1.333; background-image: url(http://www.bakertilly.co.uk/sitecollectionimages/presentation/bullet-black.gif); list-style-type: none; clear: both; float: left; width: 394.25px; background-position: 0px 0.5em; background-repeat: no-repeat no-repeat;\">dealing with HM Revenue &amp; Customs</li>\n	<li style=\"padding: 0px 0px 0px 12px; margin: 0px; line-height: 1.333; background-image: url(http://www.bakertilly.co.uk/sitecollectionimages/presentation/bullet-black.gif); list-style-type: none; clear: both; float: left; width: 394.25px; background-position: 0px 0.5em; background-repeat: no-repeat no-repeat;\">the Construction Industry Scheme</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p style=\"padding: 0px; margin: 1.333em 0px; line-height: 1.333; width: 415px; height: auto; font-family: arial, sans-serif; font-size: 12px;\">At the seminar you will have the opportunity to meet members of our employer consulting team and to discuss issues with our partners and staff.</p>\n\n<p style=\"padding: 0px; margin: 1.333em 0px; line-height: 1.333; width: 415px; height: auto; font-family: arial, sans-serif; font-size: 12px;\"><strong>Programme<br />\nTimings</strong><br />\n08.30am Registration and breakfast<br />\n09.00am Presentation<br />\n10.15am Coffee break<br />\n10.40am Presentation<br />\n12.00pm Close</p>\n\n<p style=\"padding: 0px; margin: 1.333em 0px; line-height: 1.333; width: 415px; height: auto; font-family: arial, sans-serif; font-size: 12px;\"><strong>Dates and venues</strong><br />\nBaker Tilly is running this seminar as a series across Central Scotland and the North of England.</p>\n\n<p style=\"padding: 0px; margin: 1.333em 0px; line-height: 1.333; width: 415px; height: auto; font-family: arial, sans-serif; font-size: 12px;\"><strong>North West<br />\nTuesday 16 April 2013<br />\nVenue</strong>:<br />\nThe Park Royal Hotel, Stretton Road, Stretton, Warrington, WA4 4NS<br />\n<strong>Speakers</strong>: David Heaton &amp; Gary Cryer</p>\n\n<p style=\"padding: 0px; margin: 1.333em 0px; line-height: 1.333; width: 415px; height: auto; font-family: arial, sans-serif; font-size: 12px;\"><strong>Hull<br />\nTuesday 23 April 2013<br />\nVenue</strong>: Hallmark Hotel Hull, Ferriby High Road, North Ferriby, East Yorkshire, HU14 3LG<br />\n<strong>Speakers</strong>: Jackie Hall &amp; Claire White</p>\n\n<p style=\"padding: 0px; margin: 1.333em 0px; line-height: 1.333; width: 415px; height: auto; font-family: arial, sans-serif; font-size: 12px;\"><strong>Stoke-on-Trent<br />\nWednesday 24 April 2013<br />\nVenue</strong>: Baker Tilly Office, Festival Way, Festival Park, Stoke-on-Trent, ST1 5BB<br />\n<strong>Speakers</strong>: David Heaton, Malcolm Cook &amp; Marie Black</p>\n\n<p style=\"padding: 0px; margin: 1.333em 0px; line-height: 1.333; width: 415px; height: auto; font-family: arial, sans-serif; font-size: 12px;\"><strong>Glasgow<br />\nTuesday 30 April 2013<br />\nVenue</strong>: Baker Tilly Office, Breckenridge House, 274 Sauchiehall Street, Glasgow, G2 3EH<br />\n<strong>Speakers</strong>: David Payne &amp; Emma Lambie</p>\n\n<p style=\"padding: 0px; margin: 1.333em 0px; line-height: 1.333; width: 415px; height: auto; font-family: arial, sans-serif; font-size: 12px;\"><strong>Leeds<br />\nTuesday 30 April 2013<br />\nVenue</strong>: Park Plaza Hotel, Boar Lane, City Square, Leeds, LS1 5NS<br />\n<strong>Speaker</strong>: Lesley Fidler</p>\n\n<p style=\"padding: 0px; margin: 1.333em 0px; line-height: 1.333; width: 415px; height: auto; font-family: arial, sans-serif; font-size: 12px;\"><strong>Edinburgh<br />\nWednesday 01 May 2013<br />\nVenue</strong>: Baker Tilly Office, First Floor, Quay 2, 139 Fountainbridge, Edinburgh, EH3 9QG<br />\n<strong>Speakers</strong>: Colin Brown, Alison Pryde &amp; Elizabeth Leonard</p>\n\n<p style=\"padding: 0px; margin: 1.333em 0px; line-height: 1.333; width: 415px; height: auto; font-family: arial, sans-serif; font-size: 12px;\"><strong>Newcastle<br />\nWednesday 01 May 2013<br />\nVenue</strong>: Baker Tilly Office, 1 St James&rsquo; Gate, Newcastle Upon Tyne, NE1 4AD<br />\n<strong>Speakers</strong>: Lesley Fidler &amp; Stuart McKinnon</p>\n\n<p style=\"padding: 0px; margin: 1.333em 0px; line-height: 1.333; width: 415px; height: auto; font-family: arial, sans-serif; font-size: 12px;\">To register please contact Sarah Campbell on 0161 830 4023 or email<a href=\"mailto:sarah.campbell@bakertilly.co.uk\" style=\"text-decoration: none; color: rgb(0, 119, 187);\">sarah.campbell@bakertilly.co.uk</a>&nbsp;stating which venue you wish to attend along with your name, position, company and contact details.</p>\n', '<p><span style=\"font-family: arial, sans-serif; font-size: 12px; line-height: 15px;\">The Government forces employers to act as tax collectors, loan recovery agents and state benefit distributors &ndash; all unpaid work and subject to penalties for non-compliance. In addition, penalties for late payment of in-year PAYE and the concept of &lsquo;reasonable care&rsquo; give HMRC further ways of extracting money from employers. The end of the 2012-13 tax year and the start of 2013-14 is a particularly challenging time as employers must make returns of last year&rsquo;s information whilst getting to grips with the additional responsibilities imposed by Real Time Information (RTI).</span></p>\n', '<p><span style=\"font-family: arial, sans-serif; font-size: 12px; line-height: 15px;\">The Government forces employers to act as tax collectors, loan recovery agents and state benefit distributors &ndash; all unpaid work and subject to penalties for non-compliance. In addition, penalties for late payment of in-year PAYE and the concept of &lsquo;reasonable care&rsquo; give HMRC further ways of extracting money from employers. The end of the 2012-13 tax year and the start of 2013-14 is a particularly challenging time as employers must make returns of last year&rsquo;s information whilst getting to grips with the additional responsibilities imposed by Real Time Information (RTI).</span></p>\n', 19, 86, 0, 1);
