(9, '2013-03-30 06:44:05', 'Business Class - Leeds', 'Business Class - Leeds', '<p><span style=\"font-family: arial, sans-serif; font-size: 12px; line-height: normal;\">Baker Tilly Corporate Finance is pleased to invite you to the first in a series of &lsquo;Business Class&rsquo; events to be held in Leeds. These events are a joint initiative by Baker Tilly Corporate Finance, Irwin Mitchell solicitors and Royal Bank of Scotland and are designed to address the important challenges and issues for pro-active businesses.&nbsp; Each event will cover a variety of topics that are of importance in the business world today. The first class in the series will be led by the following panellists:</span></p>\n\n<p style=\"padding: 0px; margin: 1.333em 0px; line-height: 1.333; width: 415px; height: auto; font-family: arial, sans-serif; font-size: 12px;\"><strong>Management Buy-Outs &ndash; how they work&nbsp;<br />\nJim Whittaker, Partner at Baker Tilly Corporate Finance&nbsp;</strong><br />\nJim heads up Baker Tilly&rsquo;s Lead Advisory team in Yorkshire. As an experienced Corporate Finance professional and having worked as a Finance Director in the private sector, Jim is ideally placed to give an insight into the MBO process and the common pitfalls to avoid. Jim has completed numerous MBO transactions including the buy-out of Volvox Group which was nominated for &lsquo;Deal of The Year&rsquo; in the 2012 Yorkshire Dealmaker Awards.</p>\n\n<p style=\"padding: 0px; margin: 1.333em 0px; line-height: 1.333; width: 415px; height: auto; font-family: arial, sans-serif; font-size: 12px;\"><strong>Incentivising and retaining key staff&nbsp;<br />\nSimon Cuerden and Glenn Hayes, Partners in the corporate and employment teams at Irwin Mitchell LLP</strong><br />\nThe presentation will cover common shareholder/option structures, good/bad leaver provisions, restrictive covenants, key elements of service contracts and an update on some of the wider benefits being used to incentivise key staff.<br />\nGlenn heads up the employment team in Leeds and has experience of implementing and enforcing these types of packages. Simon regularly advises on share structures and the rights attaching to them.</p>\n\n<p style=\"padding: 0px; margin: 1.333em 0px; line-height: 1.333; width: 415px; height: auto; font-family: arial, sans-serif; font-size: 12px;\"><strong>Exporting for Growth&nbsp;<br />\nCraig O&#39;Donnell, North Regional Director for Trade Finance Origination at the Royal Bank of Scotland&nbsp;</strong><br />\nCraig has responsibility for RBS&rsquo;s northern Trade Finance business development teams, focussing on the corporate and large corporate segments. Craig will cover ways in which UK businesses are looking to grow by tapping into overseas markets and exploiting new export opportunities.</p>\n\n<p style=\"padding: 0px; margin: 1.333em 0px; line-height: 1.333; width: 415px; height: auto; font-family: arial, sans-serif; font-size: 12px;\">&nbsp;</p>\n\n<table cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" style=\"font-size: 12px; border-width: 1px 0px; border-top-color: rgb(204, 204, 204); border-top-style: solid; border-bottom-color: rgb(204, 204, 204); border-bottom-style: solid; width: 344px; font-family: arial, sans-serif; line-height: normal; height: 143px;\">\n	<tbody>\n		<tr>\n			<td style=\"padding: 3px 5px 3px 0px;\"><font id=\"tmpPasteIE1360851207927\"><font id=\"tmpPasteIE1360851210965\"><strong>Time&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</strong></font></font></td>\n			<td style=\"padding: 3px 5px 3px 0px;\"><font id=\"tmpPasteIE1360851228805\">8:30am - 09:00 Breakfast and registration</font></td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td style=\"padding: 3px 5px 3px 0px;\">&nbsp;</td>\n			<td style=\"padding: 3px 5px 3px 0px;\">09:00am - 10:30 Presentations</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td style=\"padding: 3px 5px 3px 0px;\">&nbsp;</td>\n			<td style=\"padding: 3px 5px 3px 0px;\">10:30 &ndash; Close</td>\n		</tr>\n	</t