(5, 'En', 'Az', '<p>Baker Tilly Azerbaijan and Fitch Learning hosted 20 professionals from Azerbaijan Risk Professionals Association, Ata Bank, Bank of Baku, Bank Respublika, Kapital Bank, International Bank of Azerbaijan, Mugan Bank, Nikoil Bank, Paşa Holdinq, Pasha Bank, Findev Azerbaijan, DamirBank, AG Bank, Azerbaijan Industry Bank and etc. actively participated in the workshop.</p>\n', '<p>Baker Tilly Azerbaijan and Fitch Learning hosted 20 professionals from Azerbaijan Risk Professionals Association, Ata Bank, Bank of Baku, Bank Respublika, Kapital Bank, International Bank of Azerbaijan, Mugan Bank, Nikoil Bank, Paşa Holdinq, Pasha Bank, Findev Azerbaijan, DamirBank, AG Bank, Azerbaijan Industry Bank and etc. actively participated in the workshop.</p>\n\n<p>Opening of the event was realized by Mr. Ziya Ibrahimov. After greeting guests, he provided informational presentation about the Baker Tilly Azerbaijan and its activities where he operates as a Partner. Then, he gave a floor to Financial Trainer of Fitch Learning Mr. Mueen Uddeen to commence the training.</p>\n\n<p>During the workshop, Representatives of banks could improve their skills on how to categorize, measure, risk monitor and manage risks within banks, identify, categorize and quantify credit, market, liquidity, operational, legal, regulatory and reputation risks and update their skills on how the bank&rsquo;s capital is allocated to each of these risks from both a regulatory and management perspective.</p>\n\n<p>Within two full days of training, along with enjoying a highly qualified trainer, the platform of the workshop allowed bankers to to share their experiences and exchange ideas. In the end, participants were provided Certificate of Attandance by Fitch Learning and Baker Tilly Azerbaijan and took group photo.</p>\n\n<p style=\"clear:both;\"><a href=\"http://bakertilly.az/uploads/_X0A6220.JPG\" target=\"_blank\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"http://bakertilly.az/uploads/_X0A6220.JPG\" style=\"width: 200