(22, 'Seminar of existing legal framework for taxation', 'Seminar of existing legal framework for taxation', '<p>By invitation of His Excellency Mr. Kim Chang-gyu, the newly-appointed Ambassador of the Republic of Korea to Azerbaijan, Baker Tilly Azerbaijan has made a presentation at a seminar held in Marriott Hotel on November 12, 2015.</p>\n\n<p>The seminar was organized with an aim to inform all the Korean companies operating in Azerbaijan about the existing legal framework for taxation.</p>\n\n<p>The presentation made by our Senior Tax and Legal Manager Azer Akbarov was dedicated to the Overview of Taxation System in the Republic of Azerbaijan, including existing taxation regimes and details of various taxes levied in Azerbaijan.</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n', '<p><img alt=\"\" height=\"373\" src=\"http://www.bakertilly.az/images/12112015.jpg\" style=\"float: left; margin: 0px 8px 200px 0px;\" width=\"210\" />By invitation of His Excellency Mr. Kim Chang-gyu, the newly-appointed Ambassador of the Republic of Korea to Azerbaijan, Baker Tilly Azerbaijan has made a presentation at a seminar held in Marriott Hotel on November 12, 2015.</p>\n\n<p>The seminar was organized with an aim to inform all the Korean companies operating in Azerbaijan about the existing legal framework for taxation.</p>\n\n<p>The presentation made by our Senior Tax and Legal Manager Azer Akbarov was dedicated to the Overview of Taxation System in the Republic of Azerbaijan, including existing taxation regimes and details of various taxes levied in Azerbaijan.</p>\n', '<p>By invitation of His Excellency Mr. Kim Chang-gyu, the newly-appointed Ambassador of the Republic of Korea to Azerbaijan, Baker Tilly Azerbaijan has made a presentation at a seminar held in Marriott Hotel on November 12, 2015.</p>\n\n<p>The seminar was organized with an aim to inform all the Korean companies operating in Azerbaijan about the existing legal framework for taxation.</p>\n\n<p>The presentation made by our Senior Tax and Legal Manager Azer Akbarov was dedicated to the Overview of Taxation System in the Republic of Azerbaijan, including existing taxation regimes and details of various taxes levied in Azerbaijan.</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n', '<p><img alt=\"\" height=\"373\" src=\"http://www.bakertilly.az/images/12112015.jpg\" style=\"float: left; margin: 0px 8px 200px 0px;\" width=\"210\" />By invitation of His Excellency Mr. Kim Chang-gyu, the newly-appointed Ambassador of the Republic of Korea to Azerbaijan, Baker Tilly Azerbaijan has made a presentation at a seminar held in Marriott Hotel on November 12, 2015.</p>\n\n<p>The seminar was organized with an aim to inform all the Korean companies operating in Azerbaijan about the existing legal framework for taxation.</p>\n\n<p>The presentation made by our Senior Tax and Legal Manager Azer Akbarov was dedicated to the Overview of Taxation System in the Republic of Azerbaijan, including existing taxation regimes and details of various taxes levied in Azerbaijan.</p>\n', '2015-11-25 10:47:09', '', 1, 0, 0, 3, 0, 0, 0),
(25, 'Baker Tilly Azerbaijan met the graduates who earned 700 points at the entrance exams this year.', '', '<p>Today, Baker Tilly Azerbaijan met the graduates who earned 700 points at the entrance exams this year. Members of the Management Board of the company congratulated the graduates earning the highest points and wished them success in the academic year and recommended to keep the results while studying at higher education institutions.</p>\n', '<p>Today, Baker Tilly Azerbaijan met the graduates who earned 700 points at the entrance exams this year.</p>\n\n<p>Members of the Management Board of the company congratulated the graduates earning the highest points and wished them success in the academic year and recommended to keep the results while studying at higher education institutions.</p>\n\n<p>During the meeting, an open and sincere dialogue kept on the successful results and future plans of the graduates. Employees shared their experiences in the field of qualification and university, gave their advice and recommendations and promised to provide graduates with necessary support all the time.</p>\n\n<p>Baker Tilly Azerbaijan has always supported young talents, much work was done in this direction, company has participated in a number of social projects. Furthermore, the company will continue to support young talents by announcing 2018 - the &quot;Talent Year&quot; as a part of its Corporate Social Responsibility (CSR) strategy until June 2019.</p>\n\n<p>&ldquo;Baker Tilly Azerbaijan&rdquo; is a member of &ldquo;Baker Tilly International&rdquo; headquarted in London, Capital of United Kingdom, functioning in 147 countries and comprising 125 member companies. Baker Tilly International is the 9th largest accounting network in the world by fee income. The Company has been named the winner of the prestigious Network of the Year Award at The Accountant &amp; International Accounting Bulletin (IAB) awards 2016.</p>\n', '', '', '2018-06-20 23:47:42', '', 1, 0, 0, 1, 0, 0, 0),
